The National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) held a seminar on General Secretary Xi Jinping's important ideas and theories on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC.
The National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) held a seminar on General Secretary Xi Jinping's important ideas and theories on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC in Beijing from 29 to 30.
Wang Yang, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, attended the meeting and delivered a speech.
He stressed that General Secretary Xi Jinping's important thoughts on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC have profoundly expounded the status, role, goals, tasks, responsibilities and missions of the CPPCC, and practical requirements, and scientifically answered a series of directional, overall and strategic major questions, which are a powerful ideological weapon to guide the work of the CPPCC in the new era.
It is necessary to conscientiously study and implement this important thinking, grasp its great significance, rich connotation, and spiritual essence, earnestly make efforts to study, understand, and do a solid job, promote the improvement of the quality of the work of the CPPCC with theoretical study and ideological arming, and earnestly undertake the new mission of the CPPCC in the new era.
From September 29 to 30, the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) held a seminar on General Secretary Xi Jinping's important ideas and theories on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC in Beijing.
Wang Yang pointed out that since the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, General Secretary Xi Jinping has put forward a series of new ideas, new views and new assertions on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC, and for the first time proposed that the CPPCC is an important channel and special consultative body for socialist consultative democracy, an important part of the national governance system, and an institutional arrangement with Chinese characteristics. The fact that the affairs of the people are discussed by the people reveals the logical connection between the "rule of China" and China's political system, and condenses the profound theoretical thinking of upholding and developing the CPPCC system, which is the latest achievement of the party's theory of the CPPCC.
Wang Yang stressed: CPPCC at all levels should take theoretical study and discussion as an opportunity to further find out the weak links and deficiencies in CPPCC work, and make efforts to strengthen and improve them and seek breakthroughs.
It is necessary to comprehensively strengthen party building in the CPPCC system and ensure that the decisions and arrangements of the party Central Committee are implemented to the letter in the work of the CPPCC.
It is necessary to strengthen ideological and political guidance, improve the system, procedures and mechanisms for "two-way force" of advice and information and consensus building, and implement ideological and political guidance in all aspects and the whole process of performing duties.
It is necessary to focus on the central task to fulfill its duties, better obey and serve the overall situation of the party and the country, improve the quality of advice and information, and enhance the effectiveness of performing duties.
It is necessary to strengthen the building of the CPPCC itself, do a good job in the education and training of CPPCC members and cadres, give play to the basic role of the special committee, and consolidate the foundation for the CPPCC to perform its duties.
It is necessary to strengthen the guidance of the local CPPCC work, set the direction, set an example, solve difficult problems, and improve the overall level of the CPPCC work.
In order to thoroughly study and implement Xi Jinping Thought on Socialism with Chinese Characteristics for a New Era and the spirit of the 19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) has carried out the study and discussion activities of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important ideas on strengthening and improving the work of the CPPCC since May, held 8 regional forums and 7 expert and scholar symposiums, identified 18 key topics and 6 basic theoretical topics, and a total of 793,800 CPPCC members at all levels and 279,000 cadres of government agencies participated in the study and discussion, and more than 36,000 research papers were formed.
People's Daily Online, Beijing, November 5 (Wang Xiaoyan) Under the current wave of "mass entrepreneurship and innovation", more and more technology companies have begun to attach importance to patent research and development and related protection, dig deep into the potential value of patents, and occupy a leading position in the market.
Similarly, many technology companies have encountered a lot of infringement in the licensing of patented technology and the use of patented technology.
At the end of 2017, Tan Wei, He Zhanghong, and Lai Bin from Guangdong Province filed a lawsuit against Beijing Xiaoju Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Xiaoju Technology), the developer of the "Didi Chuxing" app, the operator Didi Chuxing Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Didi Chuxing), and the seller Guangdong Pacific Internet Information Service Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Guangdong Pacific) to the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court on the grounds of patent infringement.
The three plaintiffs requested the court to order the three defendants to immediately cease manufacturing, selling, offering to sell, and using the plaintiff's patent.
On October 30, 2018, the China Judgments and Judgments Network published the "Civil Ruling of the First Instance of the Invention Patent Infringement Dispute between Tan Wei, He Zhanghong et al. and Beijing Xiaoju Technology Co., Ltd. and Others", disclosing some details of the patent infringement case sued by Didi Chuxing APP.
The three plaintiffs argued that the patentee and inventor of the patent "ride-sharing service system and method based on mobile terminals", and that the entire operation process of the "ride-hailing" application in the "Didi Chuxing" app corresponded to the technical solution protected by the patent in question, which constituted patent infringement.
However, during the court's ruling, Xiaoju Technology held that Guangdong Pacific was not a qualified defendant, and that it only provided a free download of the APP "Didi Chuxing" on the Internet, and did not implement the patented method in question, and there was no direct or indirect infringement, so it should not be listed as a defendant in this case.
Second, the place of infringement in this case was not in Guangdong.
In accordance with the law, the place of infringement of the patent in question should be the place where the patent in question is fully implemented, so it raised an objection to the jurisdiction of the court and requested that the case be transferred to the court where the defendant is domiciled, that is, the Beijing Intellectual Property Court.
The Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court held that the defendant Guangdong Pacific provided the allegedly infringing Didi Chuxing APP products on its online platform, and it was not improper for the plaintiff to name the defendant Guangdong Pacific as the defendant.
In addition, the domicile of the defendant Guangdong Pacific is in Guangzhou City, which is within the jurisdiction of the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court.
The defendant Xiaoju Technology proposed to transfer the case to the Beijing Intellectual Property Court for trial, and rejected the objection raised by the defendant Xiaoju Technology Co., Ltd. to the jurisdiction of the case, and assumed the costs of accepting the jurisdiction objection case.
At present, the other trial status of the case has not been announced, and the reporter will pay close attention to the follow-up details of the Didi Chuxing patent infringement case.
Interview with the CEO of the Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation of Australia: Australia-China science and technology cooperation has achieved remarkable results
"China's science and technology have developed rapidly over the past few decades, and Australia and China can achieve great results when they work together in the field of science. ”
Larry Marshall, CEO of the Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organization of Australia, said in an exclusive interview with a reporter from China News Service in Beijing a few days ago that from the response to climate change to the cooperation of the "Sky Eye" project, Australia-China cooperation in the field of science and technology has shown great vitality.
As the largest national scientific research institution in the Australian Commonwealth, CSIRO has made many innovative research achievements in the fields of ocean, energy, biology, materials, astronomy and other fields.
CSIRO has maintained close cooperation with scientific research institutions such as the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
"It's a long-lasting friendship that encompasses trust in partners and a tradition of long-term cooperation. Marshall said.
In May this year, China's 500-meter aperture spherical radio telescope -- "China Sky Eye" -- installed the world's first 19-beam L-band receiver.
This is currently the most advanced 19-beam feed receiver in the world, which was jointly developed by Chinese and Australian scientists.
Marshall said that the successful development of the receiver is based on CSIRO's years of technology accumulation, and after it is put into use, the speed of the FAST survey will be increased by 5 to 6 times, and at the same time, more scientific observation targets will be expanded.
"This is what CSIRO is doing for FAST. ”
In addition to the above-mentioned cooperation, CSIRO also cooperates closely with Chinese scientific research institutions in the construction of the square kilometer array radio telescope, research and development of new fuel technologies, energy conservation and emission reduction.
"In the past, scientific research often focused on problems hundreds of years from now, but now more scientific research is needed to solve the problems in front of us. ”
Marshall believes that Australia and China complement each other in the field of scientific development, and both countries face a series of challenges in development.
For example, extreme weather is frequent around the world, and droughts and floods have led to reduced food production, and food shortages have seriously affected human development.
At the same time, problems such as population explosion, aging, and chronic diseases are also serious challenges.
"The cooperation between Australia and China in recent years has been focused on solving these current challenges. ”
Marshall said that the International Southern Hemisphere Marine Research Center, jointly established by CSIRO and Qingdao National Laboratory for Marine Science and Technology, focuses on observing El Niño and La Niña, studying the relationship between the two and extreme weather, and establishing early warning facilities for extreme weather.
"In the current environment, scientific and technological innovation is difficult to complete alone, requires extremely high costs, and there are many problems to be solved, so cooperation is particularly important today. ”
Marshall said that the closer the cooperation, the more likely it is to achieve breakthroughs, which is also the significance of strengthening cooperation between Australia and China under the framework of the "Belt and Road".
"Strengthening bilateral cooperation is mainly scientific and technological cooperation for us. ”
For example, Marshall said that CSIRO has recently developed a gold purification method that does not use cyanide, because the traditional cyanide gold purification method is very harmful to the environment, and many countries hope to find a gold purification method that is less polluting to the environment.
"We are very willing to introduce this technology to China, which is one of the results of our participation in the Belt and Road Initiative. ”
