North Korea's foreign minister, Ri Yong-ho, told the United Nations on Saturday that the continued imposition of sanctions deepens North Korea's distrust of the United States and that North Korea cannot unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons under such circumstances.
Mr. Ri told the U.N. General Assembly that North Korea had taken "very friendly approaches" over the past year, including halting missile and nuclear tests, dismantling nuclear test sites, and pledging not to proliferate nuclear weapons and technology.
"But we haven't seen any corresponding response from the United States," he said.
"If we don't trust the United States, we won't have confidence in our national security, and in such a situation, we can't unilaterally give up our weapons first. ”
While Ri was repeating North Korea's complaints about the United States' opposition to "phased" denuclearization, his speech was significant because it did not completely reject unilateral denuclearization, as North Korea had done before.
Mr. Lee referred to a June 12 joint statement by Kim Jong-un and Mr. Trump, in which Kim agreed to work toward the "denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula" and Mr. Trump pledged to protect North Korea's security.
North Korea has sought a formal end to the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States says it must first give up its nuclear weapons.
The United States has also rejected demands to ease international sanctions on North Korea.
"The U.S. insists on 'denuclearization first,' and increases the pressure of sanctions, uses high-pressure methods to achieve its goals, and even refuses to issue a 'declaration of the end of the war,'" Mr. Lee said.
"The idea that sanctions will make us beg for mercy on our knees is a daydream for people who don't know us.
But the problem is that this ongoing sanction is deepening our mistrust. ”
Mr. Lee did not mention the plan for a second Trump-Kim meeting that the U.S. president mentioned earlier this week at the United Nations.
Instead, he highlighted three meetings between Kim Jong-un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in in the past five months, saying: "If the other side of denuclearization were South Korea and not North Korea, then the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula would not have become so deadlocked." ”
China announced that it will reduce import tariffs on 1,585 tariff items from November 1, 2018.
Since the beginning of this year, China has taken the initiative to reduce import tariffs one after another.
On May 1 this year, the import tariff on drugs was reduced across the board, and the import tariffs on all ordinary drugs, including anti-cancer drugs, alkaloid drugs with anti-cancer effects, and Chinese patent medicines with actual imports, were adjusted to zero.
At the same time, it has also greatly reduced the value-added tax burden on the production and import of anti-cancer drugs.
On July 1, the tax on automobiles and parts of 218 tax items was reduced.
After the tax cut, China's automobile tax rate has been lower than the average level of developing countries, which is in line with the actual situation of China's automobile industry.
This tax cut will promote the structural adjustment of the industry and the optimal allocation of resources, accelerate the survival of the fittest, help improve the quality of products and services, and is expected to promote the adjustment of automobile prices to a certain extent, so that consumers can get more benefits.
On July 1, the tax on daily consumer goods under 1,449 tax items was reduced.
The tax reduction of daily consumer goods is closely related to the people's needs for a better life.
The tax reduction is not only large in number but also in force, with an average rate of 56%.
The tax reduction on consumer goods will directly benefit consumers and promote the competitiveness of domestic industries.
On November 1, 1,585 tax items such as mechanical and electrical equipment, parts and raw materials and other industrial products will be reduced.
Appropriately reducing the import tariffs on some industrial products that are urgently needed in China can attract more foreign investment, which is conducive to increasing effective domestic supply and helping industrial upgrading, and at the same time helps enterprises allocate resources on a global scale, reduce production costs, and also help reduce the pressure on the domestic environment.
According to a person in charge of the Office of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council, the above four voluntary tariff cuts, as well as the third step of tariff reduction implemented on July 1 this year in accordance with the results of the negotiations on the expansion of the scope of the information technology agreement, will reduce China's overall tariff level from 9.8 percent last year to 7.5 percent.
The adjusted overall tariff level is slightly higher than that of the European Union, lower than that of most developing countries, and at a moderately low level, which basically matches the status and development stage of China's developing countries.
According to the person in charge, as one of the important indicators of the degree of openness in China's trade in goods, the overall tariff level should be adapted to the stage of China's economic development and reflect the characteristics of the times.
China has the largest scale of trade in goods in the world, and already has an economic foundation for further opening up, but there is still a gap between the quality and efficiency of trade development and that of developed economies, so the overall level of tariffs should be appropriately reduced.
Tariffs are a means of protection for compliance, and the level of tariffs should be commensurate with industrial competitiveness, and healthy competition should be encouraged, and excessive protection is not conducive to industrial development and quality improvement.
The adjustment of tariff rates should take into account the needs of production and consumption.
Priority will be given to reducing the tax rate on commodities with greater domestic demand and conducive to industrial transformation and upgrading, and efforts will be made to increase the import of characteristic and advantageous products where the people's demand is relatively concentrated, so as to continuously enhance the sense of gain of enterprises and the public, and meet the needs of upgrading the industrial structure and consumption structure.
The intensity of tax reduction should take into account the affordability of fiscal revenue and industrial development.
In the selection of specific commodities and the scope of tariff reduction, it is necessary to make overall plans and coordinate the relationship between the two markets at home and abroad, the upstream and downstream aspects, and the relationship between production and consumption, so as to maintain the momentum of China's steady and positive economic development.
The person in charge stressed that this year is the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up, and China's initiative to reduce the overall level of import tariffs is a major measure made in accordance with China's own needs to achieve high-quality development, which is conducive to the overall use of international and foreign resources, promoting the improvement of the quality of the domestic supply system, and meeting the needs of the people's consumption upgrading.
This action and measure shows that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win strategy of opening-up, firmly support economic globalization, resolutely uphold the principle of free trade and the multilateral trading system with the WTO at its core, and continue to draw development momentum from opening up to the world, so that China's development can better benefit the world.
Serbia Announces Highest Combat Readiness Serbian and Russian presidents will meet tomorrow to discuss the situation in Kosovo
The Nantong news agency quoted the Serbian presidential office as saying that in view of the fact that the Kosovo special forces occupied the passage of the Gazivoda hydroelectric power station reservoir lake in northern Kosovo controlled by the Belgrade side, Serbian President Vučić ordered the country's armed forces to enter the highest combat readiness.
On September 29, Serbian Defense Minister Vulin declared that the Serbian army had entered a state of full combat readiness.
Vulin stressed that as long as the order issued by Vučić is still in force, Serbia will continue to monitor the current situation in Kosovo, and the Serbian army will respond no matter which direction the situation develops.
According to Russia's TASS news agency, on September 29, Vučić said in an interview that he had informed the United States, Russia, Europe and other parties of the current situation, and would go to Moscow on October 2 to meet with Russian President Putin and seek Putin's support on the Kosovo issue.
When asked if Serbia needs Russian military support like Syria, Vučić replied in the negative: "I don't want a major military conflict on our territory. ”
Vučić also said that the Serbian army has entered a state of full combat readiness only to form a deterrent to prevent the conflict from happening, but it is also a clear warning: there will be absolutely no tolerance for any violence in Kosovo.
The reason why the Serbian army has increased its combat readiness is related to two major moves by the Kosovo side.
According to the Serbian side, in recent days, Albanians have been arresting ethnic Serbs who have lived there for generations in the northern part of Kosovo, and these arrested Serbs have not violated any laws.
Vučić said that since March 26 this year, when the head of the Serbian government's office for Kosovo and Metohija, Marko Juric, was beaten and detained by Kosovo Albanian troops, ethnic Albanians have escalated the situation in the region, carrying out inhumane arrests and expulsions of Serbs.
In addition, more than 100 people, including the ROSU special forces of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Republic of Kosovo, armed police and snipers, who had been proclaimed themselves, occupied positions near the Gazivoda hydroelectric reservoir lake, entered the ecological and sports centre near the embankment in the northern part of the Kosovo region, and blocked all roads in the vicinity, which were originally controlled by the Serbian side.
Vučić pointed out that this military adventure in Kosovo was made at the instigation of Western countries, and that the Kosovo army's move was made without prior notice to the Serbian side, violating the first paragraph of Chapter IX of the "Brussels Agreement" and also violating UN Security Council Resolution 1244 and the military-technical agreement between Serbia.
Vučić has already shouted to NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg, criticizing the hypocritical rhetoric of Western countries on the Kosovo issue.
The root cause of the current conflict remains centuries-old historical feuds between the Serbs and Albans in Kosovo.
Serbs and Albanians have their own accounts of Kosovo's affiliation.
Serbia regards Kosovo as the birthplace and cradle of culture, as Serbia established its strongest state here in the 12th century, while ethnic Albanians only moved in large numbers after the Ottoman invasion and the defeat of the Serbian army to the north.
The Albanians, for their part, insist that the Illyrians, the primitive tribe that inhabited Kosovo in the 4th and 5th centuries BC, are the ancestors of the Albanians and that Kosovo has therefore been Albanian territory since ancient times.
Subjective political divisions have led to fierce clashes between different ethnicities, religions and cultures, as well as fierce antagonism between Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo.
In 1912, the Kosovo Albanians first declared the independence of Albania.
After the First World War, a large number of ethnic Albanians living in the Balkans moved to Turkey, and the proportion of Serbs increased relatively.
Kosovo became a "powder keg" in the Balkans.
In 1999, armed clashes between Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia by NATO forces against Serbia and Montenegro, and the Kosovo War broke out.
On 17 February 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared independence from Serbia.
Since then, although there has been news that Serbia will normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, due to historical and national grievances and geopolitical constraints, the agreement constrained by the United States, Europe, Russia and other forces has not been signed.
Just a month ago, Vučić made it clear for the first time that he advocated the separation of Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo, once again making the contradictions between the two communities public.
Power and communication are still interrupted, and the strong earthquake and tsunami in Indonesia are difficult
According to the figures released by the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency in the early morning of the 30th, the strong earthquake and the resulting tsunami that occurred in Donggara County, Central Sulawesi Province, the country on the 28th, have killed 420 people.
Wilem Rampangilei, head of the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency, said that the figure was only a preliminary figure for Palu, the capital of Central Sulawesi province, about 80 kilometers from the epicenter, because of the lack of large search and rescue machinery, many hotels, shopping malls, warehouses and other densely populated buildings damaged by the earthquake have not yet been searched and rescued.
On September 29, 2018 local time, a bridge damaged by an earthquake and tsunami collapsed and broke into several knots in Balu, Indonesia.
Due to severe damage to power and communication facilities, Donggara County, the epicenter, and the neighboring Xiji region are still "isolated islands" that cannot be contacted, and it is impossible to count the number of victims.
According to media reports here, Indonesian Vice President Kala said that the death toll may be in the thousands.
Power outages, communication outages, road blockages, airport damage... Rescue efforts in the aftermath of the earthquake and tsunami were difficult.
As a result of power outages, some hospitals and relief settlements in Palu rely on oil to generate electricity.
Roads in and out of the city were blocked by landslides, making it impossible for large transport vehicles, including fuel tankers, to enter, making fuel supplies very tight.
Indonesia's Social Affairs Minister Agus said that due to road damage, emergency relief materials such as tents, mattresses, blankets, clothes, food, and household kits from South Sulawesi and Gorontalo provinces, which are close to the earthquake zone, have not yet arrived in the disaster area.
Relief supplies from the capital, Jakarta, are being transported to the affected areas by Air Force transport aircraft.
In view of the damage to the control tower and runway at Palu Airport in the earthquake, all commercial flights have been grounded to ensure safety and security, and only military aircraft carrying relief supplies and personnel can take off and land.
Indonesia's Coordinating Minister for Political, Legal and Security Affairs, Wiranto, who commanded the rescue efforts in the earthquake zone, called for the restoration of power supply and commercial flight services at the airport as soon as possible to ensure the operation of hospitals and other relief agencies, so that more rescue workers, volunteers and aid supplies can reach the disaster area.
On the 28th, a number of strong earthquakes occurred in Dongara County, Central Sulawesi Province, Indonesia, among which a strong earthquake of magnitude 7.7 at 17:02 local time triggered a tsunami, causing major disasters in Palu City, Dongara County, and Siji District.
China News Service, Beijing, October 1 (Reporter Yin Li) The blue sky is like a wash, the sky is clear, and the sky is full of colorful clouds. Recently, Beijing has continued to open the most beautiful blue sky mode, attracting thousands of people in Beijing to show pictures on social platforms, and continue to swipe the screen to show their happiness, saying that "under the blue sky and white clouds, 'drunk' the beautiful skyline, this is the best business card of Beijing".
Since August, Beijing has ushered in the "bluest sky".
In the capital, people can be seen taking pictures anytime and anywhere, holding smartphones or holding SLR cameras.
On social platforms such as Weibo and WeChat Moments, you can see the Forbidden City, Tiananmen Square, Bird's Nest, Hutong in the lens of netizens everywhere... All kinds of buildings show different beauty against the blue sky.
Some netizens said that such a "scenery blockbuster" is the best city propaganda film in Beijing; some netizens joked that if such a blue sky swipes the screen for a long time, people with cervical spondylosis can be cured; and some netizens hope that "this blue can survive the winter and welcome spring and summer, so that the sky in the capital is blue all year round".
Why do the people of Beijing love to bask in the blue sky?
Just because the people who lived in the city in the past suffered from smog, so they were particularly eager for the blue sky, and after the "blue sky defense war" was launched in Beijing, the air quality continued to improve, the smog became less, the blue sky increased, and the people were happy in their eyes, and the happiness obtained was also extraordinarily weighty.
On the day of the National Day, the weather in Beijing was fine.
At 8 a.m., the vast majority of the city's 35 air quality monitoring stations were shown to be "first-class" green.
The "Blue Sky" themed photo contest spontaneously launched by the public on social platforms is still ongoing.
Why is the sky so blue in Beijing recently?
According to an official from the Beijing Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau, in August this year, the average concentration of fine particulate matter (PM2.5) in Beijing was 35 micrograms per cubic meter, setting a record for the same period in the past five years.
In September, real-time PM2.5 concentrations were in the single digits.
One of the major factors for the emergence of the "bluest sky" is the overall favorable meteorological conditions in recent times, and more importantly, Beijing's persistent air pollution control, vigorously promoting the clean air action plan in the past five years, and the continuous release of environmental benefits, so that the total amount of pollutant emissions in the region has been reduced, which has laid the foundation for continuous improvement of air quality.
In 2013, Beijing officially released and implemented the Beijing Clean Air Action Plan 2013-2017.
According to the plan, the government will continue to guide the non-capital functions to be relieved, promote clean energy substitution and pollution reduction, and eliminate a total of 4,923 coal-fired boilers.
As a result, Beijing has become the first major city in Chinese mainland to realize the full network of natural gas.
Data shows that between 2013 and 2017, the annual average PM2.5 concentration in Beijing dropped by 35.6%. The number of days meeting air quality standards increased by 50 days, the number of first-class excellent days increased by 25 days, and the number of heavily polluted days decreased by 35 days, and the incidence of heavy pollution decreased significantly.
While the air quality continues to improve, Beijing officials issued the "Three-Year Action Plan for Winning the Blue Sky Defense War in Beijing" in September this year based on a new round of PM2.5 source analysis. Resident in the capital, it is no longer "scarce and expensive", let it return to the background of people's photo albums instead of the protagonist.
During this year's National Day Golden Week, the Municipal Tourism Commission, industry and commerce, urban management, public security and other relevant departments will strengthen the law enforcement inspection of the "one-day tour" market, focusing on the chaos of the "six blacks" in tourism.
Yesterday morning, the city government held a special meeting to crack down on illegal "one-day tours" to make arrangements for the special action to further crack down on illegal "one-day tours."
At the meeting, it was revealed that focusing on the "six blacks" chaos of black ticket mention, black guides, black clubs, black cars, black shops, and black network interest chains, the city has launched a special action to crack down on illegal "one-day tours" since July 28.
Since the launch of the special action, the city has accepted a total of 39 complaints about "one-day tours", a year-on-year decrease of 63%; Since the beginning of this year, the city has accepted 270 complaints about "one-day tours", a year-on-year decrease of 62%.
In the past two months, the city has seized 248 "black cars", investigated and dealt with 158 violations of tourist passenger transport business, closed 29 shopping "black shops" and performing arts venues, investigated and dealt with 13 "black clubs" and 27 "black guides", confiscated 26,000 illegal advertisements, removed 31 illegal "one-day" billboards and 3 fake bus stop signs, investigated and dealt with 1,789 cases of various travel-related violations, 181 cases were filed by various functional departments, a heavy fine of 4.48 million yuan, and 111 people were detained for travel-related violations.
After rectification, the chaotic phenomenon of illegal "one-day tours" has been basically curbed, and the "one-day tour" market order has shown a steady and improving trend.
According to reports, in recent years, the city has continuously increased the intensity of rectification of illegal "one-day tours".
In 2016 and 2017, the Municipal Tourism Commission accepted 1,612 and 897 complaints about "one-day tours", a year-on-year decrease of 79% and 44% respectively.
Specifically, illegal solicitation of tourists on the street is called "black ticket picking", illegal websites that publish false tourist information are "black networks", travel agencies engaged in illegal "one-day tours" or institutions or individuals without travel agency business qualifications are "black companies", tour guides without tour guide certificates or illegal practices employed by "black companies" are "black guides", vehicles without tourist passenger transport qualifications used by them or vehicles with tourist passenger transport qualifications that provide passenger transport services for illegal "one-day tours" are "black cars", and finally the designated tourist shopping stores they bring tourists into are "black shops".
In this special action, the city continued to increase the illegal "day trip" fixed inspection and mobile inspection, for the illegal "day trip" high incidence and high impact of the tourist routes, the relevant departments sent a team to the car every day to accompany the group to make an unannounced visit, found evidence of violations of laws and regulations after strict investigation and punishment in accordance with the law.
Among them, "black cars" and "black shops" have become the two key points of the special operation.
According to reports, without black cars, illegal "day trips" can not be made, black cars are easy to find, remember and investigate, but also a single high value of fixed assets.
Relevant departments use road traffic monitoring probes to increase the supervision of key "one-day" routes of tourist buses, and use technical defense, physical defense and other scientific and technological intelligent means to timely discover, investigate and deal with "black cars".
Due to the small number of tourist shopping "black shops" and the fact that they operate on the ground, they have also become the focus of the crackdown.
In order to strengthen the deterrence and crackdown on illegal "one-day tours", once it is verified that there are violations of laws and regulations in the special operation, all functional departments will be given heavy and severe superimposed punishments in accordance with the law.
In August this year, the city also held a seminar on legal issues related to cracking down on illegal "one-day tours" to discuss the means and measures for combining administrative punishment with criminalization and conviction.
The Municipal Tourism Commission said that in the future, it will encourage more regular travel agencies to carry out "one-day tours" in Beijing and increase the supply of regular "one-day tours" to further occupy the living space of illegal "one-day tours".
In addition, the Municipal Tourism Commission has also continuously improved the electronic itinerary information system for tour groups to ensure that each team is included in the supervision of the electronic itinerary platform.
