China News Service Sapporo, September 30 After defeating the Cuban team 3-0 in the first game, the Chinese women's volleyball team defeated the Turkish team 3-0 again on the 30th, winning two consecutive victories in the group stage of the 2018 World Championships.
But compared with the first game, the Chinese women's volleyball team is more difficult and dangerous.
A total of 24 teams participated in the 2018 Women's Volleyball World Championship, and the Chinese women's volleyball team was in Group B with Italy, Turkey, Bulgaria, Canada and Cuba.
Judging from the world ranking and overall strength of the teams in Group B, Turkey and Italy are the main opponents of the Chinese team.
After the start of the day's game, the Chinese team entered the state quickly, took the lead at the beginning, maintained the advantage throughout the whole game, put a lot of pressure on the opponent on serve and blocking, and won the first game 25:18 relatively smoothly.
In the second game, the Turkish team served very fiercely, and took a 6:2 lead at the beginning, the Chinese team adjusted the formation after requesting a timeout, and gradually chased the score to 7 draws, and then blocked the net many times to score, playing a 7:0 scoring tide; at the end of the game, the Turkish team once chased the score to 15:19; after the Chinese team got the game point at 24:20, the tenacious Turkish team chased 2 points in a row; after the Chinese team asked for a timeout again, with Zhu Ting's running attack score, won the second game 25:23.
The situation in the third game was very stalemate, and the scores of the two sides rose alternately, and it was once tied at 19.
At the critical moment, the Turkish team made a mistake, and after the Chinese team led 21:19, it won the match point at 24:21 with Zhu Ting's strong smash and Zhang Changning's attack, and then the Turkish team chased the score to 23:24, after the Chinese team asked for a timeout, Zhang Changning scored an attack, and the Chinese team locked the victory with 25:23.
Lang Ping, head coach of the Chinese women's volleyball team, admitted frankly after the game that the whole game was not easy.
"We are well prepared, we have a good block, the Turkish team is more technical, we have to reduce our mistakes and try to win by scoring on our own. ”
