Nearly 1,000 state-owned scenic spots have lowered ticket prices, and more than half of them have dropped by more than 20%
As of September 28, 981 scenic spots have been implemented or announced to the public free opening or price reduction measures (74 free of charge, 907 price reductions), Yunnan Stone Forest, Dali Three Pagodas, Yulong Snow Mountain, Guangxi Guilin Lijiang, Fujian Wuyi Mountain, Hunan Zhangjiajie, Shaanxi Terracotta Warriors, Jiangxi Sanqing Mountain, Xinjiang Kanas and other scenic spots have implemented price reduction.
In order to implement the decisions and arrangements of the Central Economic Work Conference and the "Government Work Report", the National Development and Reform Commission issued the "Guiding Opinions on Improving the Ticket Price Formation Mechanism of State-owned Scenic Spots and Reducing the Ticket Prices of Key State-owned Scenic Spots" (hereinafter referred to as the Guiding Opinions) on June 28. Strictly implement the pricing procedures and other aspects, improve the ticket price formation mechanism of state-owned scenic spots, and ensure that the ticket prices of key state-owned scenic spots are reduced by the end of September.
In accordance with the deployment requirements, all localities have actively carried out work and have successively reduced the ticket prices of a number of key state-owned scenic spots.
As of September 28, 981 scenic spots have been implemented or issued to the public free opening or price reduction measures (74 free of charge, 907 price reductions), including 159 5A-level scenic spots, 534 4A-level scenic spots, a total of 693, accounting for 70.6%.
Among the 907 scenic spots with price reductions, 491 (54.3%) decreased by more than 20%, and 214 (23.6%) decreased by more than 30%.
Yunnan, Shandong, Guangxi, Shaanxi and other provinces have a large number of price-reducing scenic spots, of which the number of price-reducing scenic spots in Yunnan is more than 100, with an overall decrease of more than 30%.
Anhui, Chongqing and other 8 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) government pricing 5A-level scenic spots have all achieved price reduction.
Yunnan Stone Forest, Dali Three Pagodas, Yulong Snow Mountain, Guangxi Guilin Lijiang, Fujian Wuyi Mountain, Hunan Zhangjiajie, Shaanxi Terracotta Warriors, Jiangxi Sanqing Mountain, Xinjiang Kanas and other scenic spots have implemented price reductions.
The ticket prices of key state-owned scenic spots have gradually returned to a reasonable range, which is conducive to promoting the transformation and upgrading of the tourism industry from ticket economy to industrial economy, niche tourism to mass tourism, and scenic spot tourism to all-for-one tourism, and is conducive to the formation of a virtuous circle of optimization of tourism supply structure and steady expansion of tourism consumption demand, and promote the sustainable and healthy development of scenic spots and tourism.
At the same time, the National Development and Reform Commission emphasized that all localities should strengthen the price order and standardization of scenic spots, guide scenic spots to improve services, and ensure that price reductions do not reduce quality.
In addition, the National Development and Reform Commission has carried out special inspections on the recent media reflection of the problems such as the price reduction of individual scenic spots is too small and the actual drop is not reduced, requiring all localities to deal with it seriously, respond to social concerns in a timely manner, and effectively implement the price reduction in place.
IPIM has carried out short-, medium- and long-term optimization work in an orderly manner
The Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Institute (IPIM) has submitted a report on the short-, medium- and long-term optimization of "major investment immigration" and "skilled immigration".
IPIM will brief the community on the enhancement work as soon as possible.
Among them, 5 are short-term measures to be implemented this year, 5 are medium-term measures to be implemented in 2019 and 1 is a long-term measure.
In addition, IPIM has also conducted a comprehensive review of its internal management system under the direction of the Secretary for Economy and Finance, Leong Vai Tac.
The five short-term measures to be implemented this year include:
1. Carry out review work. Priority will be given to the review of cases that are about to expire for 7 years, those mentioned in the ICAC report, and new renewal cases. If a case is found to contain any inappropriate circumstances or signs of violating the law, it will be referred to the relevant judicial authorities for follow-up handling.
2. On-site inspection of projects involving "major investment immigration". By the end of September, more than 20 investment projects had been inspected;
3. Conduct a comprehensive review of the existing assessment system. In the assessment of applications for "major investment immigration", the six principles for the analysis of investment projects have been re-established, and in the assessment of applications for "skilled immigration", the relevant approval mechanism will be improved by clarifying the elements conducive to Macao's development and the conditions for giving priority to attracting talents. At the same time, a list of "five industries and 10 types of trades" has been formulated to give priority to the introduction of talents for the year, so as to tie in with the policy direction of the HKSAR Government and attract talents in a more targeted manner.
4. Increasing information transparency. These include plans to gradually announce the vetting criteria, scoring criteria and weightings from the fourth quarter of this year, and further refine and make public the vetting data;
5. In terms of improving the recognition mechanism, it has been required to check the work in Australia before confirmation, and major investments must be inspected and submitted on site.
The five medium-term measures implemented in 2019 include:
1. Establish a mechanism to regularly listen to the opinions of the Talent Development Committee and the Economic Development Committee. A working meeting was held with the Economic Development Commission in September to discuss the establishment of the mechanism.
2. Applicants are required to submit financial statements prepared by an independent third party on an annual basis to continuously review the operation of the investment project;
3. Further standardize and digitize the process of case application and approval to reduce human error;
4. Comprehensively review the current manpower allocation and implement a number of enhancement measures;
5. Intensify the study of revising the "Temporary Residence System for Investors, Managers and Technical Personnel with Special Qualifications".
As for the long-term measures, it is expected to commence the drafting of the relevant regulations in the first half of 2019 with a view to completing them as soon as possible, further clarifying the approval criteria, review mechanism and confirmation mechanism for temporary residence permits, and adding IPIM's investigative functions to more accurately vetting and supervising applications for temporary residence permits.
Experts from the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities walked into the test field and listened to the introduction of the team of academician Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
Chinanews.com, Shaya, Xinjiang, September 30 (Geng Dandan, Wang Xiaojun) Located in Shaya County, Xinjiang, the film-free cotton planting test base, the growth of film-free cotton is gratifying, compared with the mulch cotton next to it, "not inferior", clusters of snow-white cotton compete to "open", hanging full of branches.
From September 27th to 28th, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
The reporter learned at the observation meeting that the film-free cotton technology system with "Zhongmian 619" and its supporting cultivation measures as the main body has initially achieved the goal of film-free planting in cotton fields, reduced the pollution of Xinjiang cotton field residual film to the ecological environment and raw cotton, and made significant progress in the research and demonstration of film-free cotton comprehensive technology.
Academician Yu Shuxun, academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, famous cotton geneticist breeder, and chief scientist of the cotton system of the national modern agricultural industry technology system, introduced the growth of film-free cotton to Zhou Guomo, Secretary of the Party Committee of Zhejiang Agriculture and Forestry University.
"The film-free cotton comprehensive technology we developed can completely realize the planting of cotton without mulch, which can completely solve the problem of residual film pollution and achieve green cotton planting. ”
Yu Shuxun, academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, introduced.
Xinjiang is the most important cotton-producing region in China, and according to the National Bureau of Statistics, the cotton planting area in Xinjiang in 2017 was 35 million mu, accounting for 61% of the country's cotton area.
Since the introduction of plastic film into China in 1982, the area of various crops in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million mu, and the annual use of plastic film is about 300,000 tons.
Among them, the coverage rate of cotton mulch film reached 100%, and cotton field mulching accounted for about 60% of the use of mulch film in Xinjiang.
The yield of non-film cotton can be measured and the cotton yield can be 320 kg to 350 kg per mu.
With the continuous increase of plastic film input in Xinjiang, the recovery rate of residual plastic film is low, the amount of residual film in the soil is gradually increasing, and a series of problems such as soil structure damage caused by residual film have seriously affected the sustainable development of agriculture.
The residual film not only causes serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of cotton fiber.
At present, more than one-third of Xinjiang's cotton fields have been harvested by mechanization.
In 2017, the area of machine picking cotton in Xinjiang was about 14 million mu.
In the process of harvesting cotton harvesting, a large number of broken films on the surface and cotton plants are collected, and the broken films doped in the raw cotton are difficult to remove in the raw cotton processing process, and cannot be completely removed in the subsequent textile processing process, which seriously affects the quality of textile products.
On September 28, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to solve the problem of plastic film pollution in cotton fields, simplify cotton planting technology, and improve the efficiency of cotton fields, Yu Shuxun led his team to implement the "Zhongmian 619" film-free cotton technology planting in 8 years, adding wings to the green development of Xinjiang's agriculture.
Yu Shuxun introduced that through innovative breeding ideas, a new strain of upland cotton "Zhongmian 619" with ultra-early maturity, salt and alkali tolerance, low temperature resistance and high yield has been cultivated.
"Under the condition of filmless cultivation in southern Xinjiang, Zhongmian 619 has realized a series of supporting measures such as film-free seeding machinery, improvement of seeding depth, shallow burial of dropper belt under film-free conditions, suitable seeding density screening, and reasonable chemical regulation. ”
At present, Aksu, Korla, Alar and other places have established film-free cotton demonstration bases, with a yield of 4,800 kg per hectare.
Film-free cotton planting has achieved high yield, cost saving, environmental protection, and improved comprehensive benefits.
Zhang Donghai, an agronomist at the Agricultural Science Institute of the Third Division of the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through the research and demonstration of film-free cotton cultivation technology in the past six years, the yield of film-free cottonseed cotton can fully achieve a yield of 320 kg to 350 kg per mu, or even higher.
"There is great prospect for the promotion of film-free cotton cultivation technology. ”
Zhang Donghai believes that at present, the film-free cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but there is still a certain gap between the current economic benefits and the plastic film cultivation.
"The support of cotton purchase price will be conducive to future promotion. ”
Yu Shuxun said that in the next step, he and his team will continue to conduct in-depth research and large-scale promotion and application of film-free cotton, make the film-free cotton industry bigger and stronger, and completely solve the problem of soil pollution caused by plastic film.
