The State Administration for Market Regulation recently issued the "Notice on Strengthening Market Price Supervision during the Mid-Autumn Festival and National Day in 2018", which requires that price supervision in the field of housing rental and real estate should be strengthened, and price violations such as collusion in rent prices, hoarding rental housing, fabricating and hyping false information to raise rents, arbitrary charges in the form of bundled services, misleading price information, and unclear price marking.
The notice made it clear that it is necessary to strengthen price monitoring and early warning and pay close attention to market price dynamics.
All localities should pay close attention to the market and price changes of daily necessities such as grain, oil, meat, poultry, eggs, vegetables, milk, and salt, as well as the special commodities consumed by local residents during festivals, and strengthen price monitoring, analysis, and early warning.
Once the tendency and symptomatic problems of market fluctuations are discovered, timely measures will be taken to effectively resolve them.
It is necessary to strengthen the supervision and inspection of the wholesale and retail links of daily necessities, increase the frequency of monitoring and supervision of supermarkets, farmers' markets and other places closely related to the daily consumption of the masses, and urge operators to abide by the law and operate in good faith.
The circular pointed out that it is necessary to strengthen inspections in key areas and create a good environment for festival consumption; strengthen the supervision and control of ticket prices in state-owned scenic spots; focus on investigating and dealing with violations of laws and regulations such as state-owned scenic spots not implementing the price level or floating range stipulated by the government, adding additional charging items without authorization, raising ticket prices in disguised form by setting up "park within a park" tickets in violation of regulations, high pricing and large discounts, bundling sales, not clearly marking prices in accordance with regulations, not implementing preferential measures, increasing prices outside the price, and forcing fees to be collected on behalf of others.
The circular demanded that the price control of daily necessities, especially agricultural products, should be strengthened.
Affected by seasonal changes, natural disasters and sudden epidemics, the prices of vegetables, pork and other essential agricultural products have fluctuated in some areas recently.
All localities should conscientiously strengthen the supervision of market prices of agricultural and sideline products in light of the actual local conditions, cooperate with relevant departments to do a good job in stabilizing production and market supply, and organize forces to carry out key market inspections and random spot checks.
For pork and other commodities whose supply is tight and the price has risen rapidly, the frequency of inspections will be increased, and illegal acts such as hoarding, price gouging, and collusion to raise prices will be seriously investigated and punished.
The circular pointed out that it is necessary to strengthen price supervision in the field of housing rental and real estate.
The Mid-Autumn Festival and the National Day coincide with the peak season for housing leasing and commercial housing sales, and all localities should pay close attention to the price behavior of real estate enterprises, intermediary companies and housing leasing-related enterprises, and strictly rectify the price collusion of rent prices, hoarding rental housing, fabricating and hyping false information to raise rents, charging arbitrarily in the form of bundled services, publishing misleading price information, and unclear price marking, and increase the inspection of the price of hot-selling real estate and real estate intermediaries on sale. Behaviors that disrupt market order are investigated and dealt with, the real estate market environment is purified, and an open and transparent real estate market price order is created.
The notice mentioned that all localities should earnestly do a good job in price supervision in other aspects of the tourism industry, strive to standardize the price order of catering, accommodation, shopping, sightseeing, entertainment, parking and other links, guide operators to do a good job in clearly marking prices and publicizing charges, and seriously investigate and deal with all kinds of price violations.
The circular indicated that it is necessary to strengthen the inspection of the prices of highways, railways, civil aviation, water transport, and other transportation vehicles, and seriously investigate and deal with illegal acts such as illegal price increases, off-price charges, and failure to clearly mark prices in accordance with regulations.
Implement the "green channel" for the transportation of fresh agricultural products and the policy of exempting small passenger cars from tolls on major holidays.
It is necessary to innovate regulatory means and working methods, strengthen the publicity of price laws and regulations for online and offline commodity retail enterprises and e-commerce platforms, urge operators to improve price promotion plans, and investigate and deal with illegal acts such as fictitious original prices, misleading price labels, and non-performance of price commitments in accordance with the law.
