The reporter learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission, and the Ministry of Commerce recently jointly issued a notice that in order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, the profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China are used for domestic direct investment, and the scope of application of the policy of temporarily exempting withholding income tax is expanded from foreign investment encouraged projects to all projects and fields that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
This policy is effective from January 1, 2018.
The circular clarifies that the direct investment made by foreign investors with shared profits includes equity investments such as capital increases, new constructions, and equity acquisitions by foreign investors with shared profits, but does not include new additions, transfers, and acquisitions of shares of listed companies other than qualified strategic investments.
If a foreign investor is entitled to the policy of temporarily withholding tax in accordance with the provisions but does not actually enjoy it, it may apply for retroactive enjoyment of the policy and refund the tax paid within three years from the date of actual payment of the relevant tax.
In addition, after a foreign investor enjoys the prescribed policy of temporary withholding tax exemption, if the investee enterprise is restructured and meets the conditions for special restructuring and is actually subject to tax treatment in accordance with the special restructuring, it can continue to enjoy the policy of temporary withholding tax exemption.
In order to ensure that the profits of foreign investors are actually used for direct investment, the circular stipulates that if the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds shall be transferred directly from the account of the profit-distributing enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and shall not be turned over in other accounts at home and abroad before the direct investment; If the payment is made in non-cash forms such as securities, the ownership of the relevant assets shall be transferred directly from the profit-distributing enterprise to the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and shall not be held or temporarily held by other enterprises or individuals before direct investment.
The circular also requires the tax authorities to strengthen follow-up management in accordance with the law.
If a foreign investor has enjoyed the policy of temporarily withholding tax and does not meet the prescribed conditions after subsequent management by the tax department, it shall be deemed that the foreign investor has failed to declare and pay enterprise income tax in accordance with the regulations, except for the liability of the enterprise for profit distribution, and will be investigated for the liability for tax delay in accordance with the law, and the tax delay payment period shall be calculated from the date of payment of the relevant profits.
The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) said Friday that it would no longer allow imports of APIs made by China's Huahai Pharmaceutical and preparations made from the company's APIs.
A drug previously manufactured by Huahai Pharmaceutical was recalled due to the presence of a probable carcinogen.
The European Medicines Agency said it was considering further action against other ingredients produced by the drug.
