Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said in a speech at the Council on Foreign Relations on Friday that China-US relations have once again reached a crossroads, and if the two sides can look at each other positively and inclusively, expand and deepen positive cooperation, and properly manage differences and contradictions, they can open up better prospects.
"The U.S.-China relationship is our common asset and needs to be taken care of together. ”
