Wang Yi also stressed once again that China will definitely embark on a different development path from that of traditional major countries.
This path with Chinese characteristics determines that China will not and cannot repeat the mistake of being a strong country and must be hegemonic, and it also determines that China will neither become the United States, nor will it challenge the United States, let alone replace the United States.
