Beijing News (Reporter Ni Wei) The State Administration of Radio, Film and Television issued the "Notice on Carrying out Special Rectification Work on Radio and Television Advertising" on September 29, and will carry out special rectification work on radio and television advertising from now until the end of this year.
The content of rectification includes advertisements with vulgar content, low style and taste, and problematic medical and health programs broadcast without record management.
According to the notice, the focus of this special rectification work is to find and rectify nine aspects.
Specifically, it includes: advertisements with problems with orientation, advertisements with vulgar content, low style, and low taste; advertisements with problems of overtime and overtime and non-compliance with regulations; advertisements for medical treatment, medicines, medical devices, health foods, cosmetics, and beauty that are exaggerated, exaggerated, falsely publicized, misleading the audience, or released in disguised form as programs, and medical and health programs that are broadcast without filing and management; merchants and franchises with problems of exaggerating and exaggerating false publicity, misleading the audience, and luring the audience to be deceived; Advertisements with expected returns on investment, such as for investment and financial management, collectibles, etc., advertisements that induce minors to have negative behaviors or form negative values, harming minors' physical and mental health, and other issues, where the duration and frequency of public service advertisements do not meet the requirements of the regulations, where there are problems of imperfect management systems for advertising broadcasts, lax review and control, and inadequate implementation of responsibilities; and advertisements that have other problems of violating laws and regulations.
The rectification work will be fully covered throughout the country, and the requirements of rectification and standardization will be fully implemented in all levels of radio and television media, all channel frequencies, all program columns and time periods, "leaving no blind spots, no dead ends, and no exceptions".
The circular requires that all levels of administrative departments for radio and television should handle all kinds of advertisements that violate laws and regulations discovered during supervision and inspection in strict accordance with the State Administration's "Measures for Handling Violations by Radio and Television Broadcasting Institutions".
Where the circumstances of the violation are serious, they should be given serious punishments such as admonishment talks, circulating criticism, suspending the broadcast of advertisements or even suspending the broadcast of frequency channels, and publicly expose them to the public in light of the circumstances.
In recent years, the State Administration of Radio, Film and Television has repeatedly stopped illegal advertisements.
This year, the State Administration of Radio and Television issued a notice to publicly stop advertisements with serious violations such as "0 bubble fruit milk", "sava cocktail" and "Bangruite plant anti-hair loss lotion", which have serious violations such as bias and exaggerated and exaggerated propaganda and misleading audiences.
The State Administration of Radio, Film and Television has formulated a number of regulations and notices to regulate radio and television broadcast advertising.
The "Notice on Further Strengthening the Management of TV Shopping Short Advertisements Broadcast by Satellite TV Channels" stipulates that all satellite TV channels are not allowed to broadcast TV shopping short advertisements from 18 o'clock to 24 o'clock every day.
When broadcasting TV shopping short advertisements during other periods, the host must not be used for publicity, and "selling" exaggerated dubbing, intonation, movements, etc. must not be used for publicity, and "orthopedics", "shaping", "translucent", "fat throwing" and other propaganda or disguised publicity of breast enhancement and weight loss products must not be used, and no more than 1 (times) of TV shopping short advertisements shall be broadcast every hour every day, and each shall not exceed 3 minutes.
The "Notice on Further Strengthening the Administration of Radio and Television Advertising Broadcasting" stipulates that when inserting advertisements in the middle of film and television dramas, television stations must strictly abide by the provisions of Order No. 61 of the General Administration: two commercial advertisements may be inserted in each episode (calculated as 45 minutes) during non-prime time, and the duration of each episode shall not exceed 1 minute and 30 seconds;
The circular also stipulates that radio and television broadcasters shall strictly examine the qualifications, certificates and other statutory materials for health information advertisements such as medical treatment, medicines, medical devices, and health foods, and resolutely prohibit the broadcast of sex-related advertisements.
It is necessary to standardize the form of health information advertising, and advertisements must not be published in disguised form in the form of health information special programs.
Health information programs shall focus on the introduction of scientific knowledge such as disease prevention, control, and treatment, and must not contain advertising content such as for medical treatment, medicines, medical devices, and health foods, and must not be testified in the name of patients, doctors, pharmacists, experts, and so forth.
