China News Service Fuzhou, September 30 (Reporter Long Min) The sixth meeting of the Standing Committee of the 13th Fujian Provincial People's Congress voted to pass the "Regulations on Promoting the Construction of Ecological Civilization in Fujian Province" on the 30th.
"Lucid waters and lush mountains are invaluable assets" was written into the legislation of Fujian Province for the first time, and it has become an operable and enforceable regulation throughout the entire regulations.
Fujian is China's first national ecological civilization pilot zone.
The person in charge of the Legislative Affairs Office of the Fujian Provincial People's Government said that it is very necessary and urgent to form a basic regulation on the construction of ecological civilization from the overall and overall situation, so as to solve the problem of relying solely on scattered laws, regulations, and policy documents to regulate and control the construction of ecological civilization, and also to provide a legal basis for formulating and promulgating relevant regulations, normative documents, and measures.
The regulations fully reflect the characteristics of Fujian, and transform the mature experience and practices in the practice of ecological civilization construction into the form of laws and regulations for promotion and implementation: such as the replicable and generalizable "Changting experience" formed by Fujian's soil and water conservation management work, The regulations summarize and improve the experience of soil and water conservation management in Fujian Province, stipulating that local people's governments at or above the county level shall strengthen unified leadership over soil and water conservation work, and demarcate key soil erosion prevention areas and treatment areas according to the results of soil erosion investigations;
The regulations stipulate that a lifelong accountability system for ecological and environmental damage shall be implemented.
Where the requirements of scientific development are violated and serious damage to ecological and environmental resources is caused, the principal leading cadres and relevant responsible persons who bear leadership responsibility shall be held accountable for life.
According to reports, the "Regulations on the Promotion of Ecological Civilization Construction in Fujian Province" will come into force on November 1 this year.
China and Pakistan agreed to complete the economic corridor projects under construction in a timely manner and speed up the construction of the Gwadar port
China and Pakistan agreed to further consolidate and expand economic ties between the two countries, the Chinese Foreign Ministry said on Sunday.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen their strategic partnership.
The two sides reaffirmed their "commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor" and "oppose negative propaganda against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor".
China's Ministry of Foreign Affairs was quoted by Reuters as saying that China and Pakistan would "strengthen practical cooperation in trade and investment, and upgrade Pakistan's industrial capacity through the establishment of joint ventures in priority areas, the transfer of labor-intensive industries and the development of cooperation with small and medium-sized enterprises."
According to a press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the two sides agreed to complete the projects under construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor in a timely manner, accelerate the construction of the Gwadar port and supporting projects, focus on economic and social development, create jobs and improve people's livelihood, and accelerate cooperation in industries and parks and agriculture.
The two sides also agreed to conclude the second phase of the China-Pakistan FTA negotiations as soon as possible and continue to advance the negotiations on the China-Pakistan Agreement on Trade in Services. ”
In a joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the CPEC and agreed that CPEC is a win-win cooperation plan that will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region.
The two sides agreed that the Gwadar port is an important node for cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to speed up the construction of the Gwadar port port and supporting projects.
China and Pakistan also said in a joint statement that they oppose negative propaganda about the CPEC.
The two sides agreed to establish a strategic dialogue between the foreign ministers of China and Pakistan and to restructure the original strategic dialogue at the level of deputy foreign ministers into diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level visits between the two militaries and exchanges between various departments and levels.
In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, the Ministry of Finance and other four ministries and commissions of the People's Republic of China jointly announced that starting from 1 January 2018, the scope of application of the policy of temporarily exempting the withholding tax on profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China for domestic direct investment will be expanded from foreign investment encouraged projects to all projects and fields that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
According to a notice published on the website of the Ministry of Finance, several conditions must be met for foreign investors to temporarily exempt them from withholding tax, including direct investment by foreign investors with shared profits, including equity investments such as capital increases, new constructions, and equity acquisitions carried out by foreign investors with shared profits, but excluding new additions, transfers, and acquisitions of shares of listed companies (except for qualified strategic investments).
It also includes dividends, bonuses and other equity investment income derived from the actual distribution of realized retained earnings by resident enterprises in China to investors.
In addition, if the profits used by foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds shall be transferred directly from the account of the profit-distributing enterprise to the account of the investee enterprise or the equity transferor, and shall not be turned over in other accounts at home or abroad before the direct investment;
The notice also stated that foreign investors who actually recover their direct investments that enjoy the benefits of the withholding tax policy through equity transfer, repurchase, liquidation, etc., shall declare the deferred tax to the tax authorities in accordance with the prescribed procedures within 7 days after the actual receipt of the corresponding amounts.
In order to encourage foreign investors to continue to invest and operate in China, the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China jointly issued a notice at the end of 2017 to implement a tax deferral policy and temporarily waive withholding tax on profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China that are directly invested in encouraged investment projects from 1 January 2017.
The executive meeting of the State Council of China decided last week to expand the scope of the temporary exemption from withholding tax on foreign reinvestment from encouraged foreign investment projects to all non-prohibited projects and fields, so as to further strengthen the protection of intellectual property rights.
The reporter learned from the National Health Commission that compared with a few decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in China has decreased, but the incidence of overweight and obesity has increased significantly.
Experts pointed out that the most important concept of maintaining a healthy weight is to "cure the disease before it happens", and vigorously promote scientific fitness and reasonable diet.
According to the "Core Information and Interpretation of Health Education for Chinese Adolescents (2018 Edition)" recently released by the National Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is a reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Overweight, obesity, and blind weight loss are all bad for your health.
The health hazards behind the "little chubby dun" cannot be ignored.
Ding Gangqiang, director of the Institute of Nutrition and Health of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said that overweight and obesity endanger the normal growth and development of adolescents, adversely affect their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence, and even lead to high blood pressure, high blood sugar and high blood lipids in children.
At the same time, overweight and obesity in adolescents tend to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes in adulthood.
Ding Gangqiang said that the 2010-2012 nutrition and health test of Chinese residents showed that the overweight rate of children and adolescents aged 6-17 in China was 9.6 percent, and the obesity rate was 6.4 percent, and the sum of the two was 16 percent.
At the same time, the overweight and obesity of children and adolescents are higher than that of boys and girls, and that of urban children and adolescents is higher than that of rural areas, and the rate of overweight and obesity has increased significantly in recent decades.
How can adolescents cope with overweight and obesity?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion Research Center of the General Administration of Sports, pointed out that the main reasons for obesity among adolescents are excessive caloric intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this simple obesity, we should pay attention to scientific exercise and reasonable dietary control.
Zhang Li pointed out that the most important concept of maintaining a healthy weight is to "cure the disease before it happens", and a very important part of it is to carry out all-round science education for schools, parents and students, popularize the dangers of overweight and obesity, and improve the awareness of teenagers.
Adolescents should have regular physical examinations, monitor growth and development indicators such as height and weight, and detect and scientifically judge whether overweight and obesity occur as early as possible, so as to take timely interventions.
For adolescents who are already overweight and obese, Ding Gangqiang suggested that in addition to actively and scientifically arranging meals and exercises, adolescents are in a special physiological stage, and should avoid using hunger or semi-starvation therapy to control and lose weight, and must not blindly take weight loss drugs.
Sep 28 (Reuters) - Facebook (FB. O) said Friday that hackers stole digital login codes that gave them access to nearly 50 million user accounts, an unprecedented security breach in its history.
Facebook, which has more than 2.2 billion monthly users, said it had not yet determined whether attackers were abusing any accounts or stealing personal information.
The company also did not find the location of the hackers and was not sure if the hackers targeted specific victims.
Initial analysis suggests that it was a widespread attack.
CEO Mark Zuckerberg called the incident "really serious" in a media conference call.
A spokesman for the company said his account, as well as that of Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg, was also affected.
Facebook shares fell 2.6 percent on Friday, dragging down major Wall Street stock indexes.
U.S. lawmakers said Friday that the attack could increase calls for data privacy legislation.
"This is yet another sad piece of evidence that Congress needs to step in to protect the privacy and security of social media users," Democratic Senator Mark Warner said in a statement.
Federal Trade Commission (FTC) Commissioner Rohit Chopra tweeted that I would like to receive an answer to Reuters' coverage of the security breach.
Changsha, September 30 (Zheng Yuliang, Tian Can) September 30 is China's fifth Martyrs' Memorial Day.
On such a special day, the families of Hunan Anti-Japanese War veterans, representatives of the Revolutionary Party of the Kuomintang, representatives of the homes of Hunan veterans and other people from all walks of life came to the "Tang Dynasty Longevity Garden - Anti-Japanese War Theme Park" in Changsha City to participate in the collective burial ceremony of Hunan Anti-Japanese War veterans on the 2018 Martyrs' Memorial Day, and bid farewell to the partners of 10 Anti-Japanese War veterans and 4 Anti-Japanese War veterans.
"The veterans of the Anti-Japanese War are the witnesses of China's Anti-Japanese War and the true, vivid and vivid teaching materials of patriotism. ”
Liu Xiao, former vice chairman of the Hunan Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, said that the heroic and selfless patriotic spirit of the veterans of the Anti-Japanese War is a precious spiritual wealth for the contemporary Chinese people.
Zhu Jianjun, vice chairman of the Changsha CPPCC and chairman of the Changsha Municipal Committee of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, pointed out in his speech that in recent years, the "Care for Anti-Japanese War Veterans" project has provided caring services for Anti-Japanese War veterans through living subsidies, free pensions, free burials and other forms, and has become an excellent brand in the social service work of the Changsha Civil Revolution.
He believes that only by instilling history in our hearts can we pass on the spirit of the War of Resistance Against Japanese Aggression.
At 11 o'clock in the morning, in the solemn and heavy music, the people who came to participate in the event stood solemnly.
The members of the Tang Dynasty Etiquette Team wore ceremonial dresses, held flowers in their arms, and walked in a neat queue to bid farewell to 10 Anti-Japanese War veterans and the partners of 4 Anti-Japanese War veterans.
Participants laid flowers and paid respects to the veterans of the Anti-Japanese War, and there were many children in the crowd who paid tribute to the heroes of the Anti-Japanese War with their parents.
"Tang Dynasty Longevity Garden, Anti-Japanese War Theme Park" is the first cemetery with the theme of the Anti-Japanese War jointly created by the Changsha Municipal Committee of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang and Hunan Tang Dynasty Longevity Garden Co., Ltd., which was completed in 2014.
The first phase of the cemetery covers an area of more than 2,000 square meters, consisting of "Heroes Immortal Monument", "Victory Square", "Anti-Japanese War Heroes Cemetery" and other parts.
The "Anti-Japanese War Heroes Cemetery" provides a cemetery for the Hunan Anti-Japanese War heroes free of charge, and is praised as "the last military camp for the veterans of the Anti-Japanese War".
Every year around Qingming and National Day, the cemetery will hold large-scale public sacrifices and burial ceremonies.
Since 2015, seven collective burial ceremonies for veterans of the Anti-Japanese War have been held here, and 102 veterans of the Anti-Japanese War and their partners have been buried here.
Yichang, October 1 (China News Service) -- The newly revised "Three Gorges-Gezhouba Water Conservancy Hub Navigation Dispatching Regulations" (hereinafter referred to as the "Scheduling Regulations") was officially implemented on October 1, and the Three Gorges ship lift was officially dispatched with the ship lock after two years of trial navigation.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the waters of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba were in good order.
The Three Gorges Navigation Administration of the Yangtze River issued the first security inspection plan at 21 o'clock on September 30, and conducted security inspections on 160 ships, and a total of 124 ships passed the security inspection.
At 14 o'clock on October 1, the general aviation department arranged the first gate crossing plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security inspection plan will be issued once a day at 9 a.m. and 9 p.m., and the dam crossing plan will be released once a day at 2 p.m. and 8 p.m. each day, so that ships can flexibly arrange the dam crossing plan.
The "Dispatching Regulations" adds the principle of "classified control" for ship dam crossing scheduling, clarifies the priority order of ships passing through the dam according to the functional positioning of the lock and ship lift, and adjusts the short-line passenger ship passing through the lock to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the integrity ship.
This is also the second year after the trial operation of the ship lift, and it is officially unified with the lock.
The large-length-wide demonstration ships and new energy powered ships in the Sichuan River and Three Gorges reservoir areas have also been ranked as priority for the first time.
At the same time, the "Dispatching Regulations" adjusted the "navigable dispatching and management waters" from the previous 180 kilometers of near-dam waters to 541.8 kilometers of waters from Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to Shishou Yangtze River Bridge, and divided into "core waters, near-dam waters, controlled waters, and dispatching waters".
This is conducive to the selection of suitable water areas to be locked, and to reduce the backlog of ships waiting for locks in the dam area.
According to the current characteristics of ships crossing the dam and waiting for the lock, the "Dispatching Regulations" also put forward integrity restraint measures such as canceling the declaration of ships that violate the rules and delaying the dam crossing for 24 hours.
After the impoundment of the Three Gorges, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, which has promoted the rapid development of shipping on the Yangtze River.
According to the data, the annual cargo throughput of the Three Gorges Locks and Gezhouba Locks increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017, respectively.
In the two years since the Three Gorges ship lift was put into trial operation, 5,767 ships, 162,200 passengers and 1,712,800 tons of freight have been passed.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Administration, said that the "Dispatching Regulations" have a positive effect on promoting the management of honest gate crossing, maintaining the navigation order of the two dam hubs, relieving the pressure of ships waiting for the gate in the dam area, and improving the navigation capacity.
