With the approval of Premier Li Keqiang, the State Council recently issued the "Decision on Further Reducing the Management Catalogue of Industrial Product Production Licenses and Simplifying the Approval Procedures".
The "Decision" proposes to further reduce the catalogue of industrial product production license management, cancel the management of 14 types of industrial product production licenses, and delegate the management authority of 4 types of industrial product production licenses to the quality and technical supervision departments of provincial people's governments.
After this reform, the number of products subject to the management of industrial product production licenses will be reduced from 38 categories last year to 24 categories at present.
The "Decision" clarifies that the approval procedures for the products in the catalogue shall be simplified.
The first is to change the pre-certification product inspection organized by the issuing authority to the product inspection report issued by the qualified inspection and testing agency submitted by the enterprise when applying.
Second, in addition to hazardous chemicals, the provincial people's government quality and technical supervision department (market supervision and management department) to implement the license of the product after the implementation of on-site review, enterprises to submit the application and product inspection report and make a commitment to ensure product quality and safety, after the formal examination can be obtained production license, and then within the specified time to accept the on-site review.
Third, if the enterprise produces and operates different categories of products in the catalog, in accordance with the principle of "one enterprise, one license", when applying for a new license or applying for a renewal of the license, a license will be reviewed and issued together.
The "Decision" requires that all regions and relevant departments should solidly promote the work of reducing the catalogue and simplifying the approval procedures.
Intensify the publicity of enterprise commitments and post-on-site review, strengthen credit supervision and restraint measures, implement the main responsibility of enterprise quality, and revoke production licenses for false promises and non-compliance with requirements.
For the cancellation of industrial product production license management products, to strengthen the supervision during and after the event, involving public health and safety, environmental protection and other products can be converted into compulsory certification, a positive list and publicize to the public, unified certification standards, reasonable reduction and certification of testing items, compulsory certification costs in principle by all levels of finance according to the system to bear.
Adopt support measures to encourage enterprises to carry out voluntary certification, promote the establishment of brands and expand markets.
It is necessary to benchmark against international advanced standards and promote the improvement of industrial product quality.
Give full play to the role of third-party social organizations to ensure the quality and safety of industrial products.
For products that retain the management of industrial product production licenses, it is necessary to improve the standard system, give full play to the advantages of industry supervision, strengthen the responsibility of "who approves and who supervises", dynamically assess product quality and safety risks, and reduce the catalog in a timely manner, delegate approval authority or transfer to certification management.
China's composite PMI rose month-on-month in September, and the manufacturing PMI fell month-on-month.
According to data released by the National Bureau of Statistics of China on the 30th, in September, China's composite PMI output index was 54.1%, 0.3 and 0.1 percentage points higher than the previous month and annual average, indicating that the production and business activities of Chinese enterprises remained stable overall.
In the same month, the manufacturing production index and the non-manufacturing business activity index, which constitute the composite PMI output index, were 53.0% and 54.9% respectively, down and rising month-on-month.
Among them, China's manufacturing PMI was 50.8%, down 0.5 percentage points from the previous month.
Zhao Qinghe said that this month's manufacturing PMI has five main characteristics:
First, the fundamentals of the manufacturing industry are generally stable.
Among the 21 industries surveyed, the PMI of 14 industries is located in the expansion range, of which the PMI of manufacturing industries such as medicine, special equipment, and electrical machinery and equipment are all at a high operating level of more than 53.5%, with a rapid growth rate.
Second, supply and demand fluctuate slightly.
The production index and new orders index were 53.0% and 52.0%, down 0.3 and 0.2 percentage points respectively from the previous month, and supply and demand continued to maintain a boom state, but the expansion slowed down slightly.
The new export orders index and import index were 48.0 percent and 48.5 percent, respectively 1.4 and 0.6 percentage points lower than the previous month, and the prosperity fell to the low point of the year.
Fourth, the cost of raw material procurement has increased.
The purchase price index of major raw materials was 59.8 percent, up 1.1 percentage points from the previous month, and the ex-factory price index was 54.3 percent, the same as the previous month, both of which were the highest points of the year.
Fifth, large enterprises are operating steadily, and the operating conditions of small enterprises continue to improve.
The PMI of large enterprises was 52.1 percent, the same as the previous month, and the index has been in the expansion range of 52.0 percent and above since the beginning of this year, and the production index and the new orders index have increased month-on-month this month, which is the main driving force for the manufacturing industry to maintain expansion; the PMI of medium-sized enterprises was 48.7 percent, 1.7 percentage points lower than that of the previous month, and was in the contraction range; the PMI of small enterprises was 50.4 percent, 0.4 percentage points higher than that of the previous month, rising for two consecutive months.
In the same month, China's non-manufacturing business activity index was 54.9 percent, up 0.7 percentage points from the previous month, rebounding for two consecutive months.
Zhao Qinghe believes that the non-manufacturing industry as a whole continues to maintain a steady and positive development momentum.
The business activity index of road transport, securities, real estate and other industries continued to be below the critical point, and the total business volume decreased.
NAGOYA, Nov 5 (Reuters) - Bank of Japan (BOJ) Governor Haruhiko Kuroda said on Monday that the central bank is aware that a prolonged ultra-loose monetary policy could squeeze financial institution profit margins and could destabilize the country's banking system.
But he said the BOJ needs to maintain its massive stimulus program while keeping a close eye on the pros and cons of its policies, given low inflation and uncertainty in overseas economies.
"The Bank of Japan fully acknowledges that the strength of financial institutions will be increasingly affected by continued monetary easing," Kuroda said in a speech to business leaders in Nagoya.
He said that if financial institutions were more risk-taking to compensate for years of low interest rate shrinking margins, there was a risk of turmoil in the banking system in the event of a severe negative shock.
"Although these risks are not significant at the moment, the central bank will closely monitor the situation and encourage financial institutions to take the necessary measures," he said.
The minutes of the BoJ meeting, released earlier on Monday, showed that at the September meeting, the BOJ's policy committee discussed the rising costs of long-term easing.
According to the minutes, one member said that if the economy continues to expand, "the Bank of Japan has more room for policy flexibility in the future." ”
Another member said that the committee should discuss how long the BOJ can maintain its stimulus, given the limits of the duration of the policy, according to the minutes.
Kuroda said the Bank of Japan will assess the financial risks posed by easing policy, while also taking into account the uncertainty surrounding the outlook for the Japanese economy, as trade frictions between China and the United States and rising protectionism could affect global demand.
"The impact of such issues on the Japanese economy is limited for the time being," Kuroda said.
"But if the problem continues, the impact on the Japanese economy may become greater," he added.
"There is a need for continued strong monetary easing, while considering the positive and negative effects in a balanced way," Kuroda said.
Despite the growing drawbacks of the aggressive stimulus program, such as the erosion of financial institutions' profits by prolonged low interest rates, low inflation has forced the Bank of Japan to maintain the program.
The Bank of Japan maintained monetary policy last month, and Kuroda ruled out a near-term interest rate hike in the face of risks posed by the global trade war.
June 1, 2018, Cardiff, USA, the corporate logo on Tesla's electric vehicles.
Under a settlement, Tesla Motors and its chief executive, Elon Musk, have agreed to pay a $20 million fine to financial regulators each, and Musk will also step down as chairman of the company but remain as CEO.
The settlement will cap two months of turmoil for Tesla.
The Securities and Exchange Commission's disclosure on Saturday of the settlement of securities fraud allegations will bring investors a sigh of relief.
Investors had feared that the protracted legal battle would only further hit the still loss-making electric car company.
The SEC sued Musk on Thursday for fraud, saying his August 7 tweet misled investors.
The tweet said he was considering taking Tesla private for $420 per share and had secured financing.
The SEC said the tweets were actually unfounded and that the market turmoil they caused hurt investors.
Investors and corporate governance experts say the deal could strengthen Tesla, which has been hit hard by Musk's recent behavior.
Steven Heim, head of Boston Common Asset Management, said the settlement should put Musk under more scrutiny without taking the "devastating" steps to kick him out of Tesla.
The asset manager holds shares in Panasonic, Tesla's battery maker.
Under the proposed agreement, Tesla would have to appoint an independent chairman, two independent directors, and a board committee to establish controls over Musk's communications.
"It is in the best interests of our market and our investors, including Tesla shareholders, that this matter is resolved expeditiously and on agreed terms," SEC Chairman Clayton said in a statement.
Thursday's accusations wiped out about $7 billion from Tesla's market capitalization, which stood at $45.2 billion on Friday, lower than General Motors' $47.5 billion.
In the settlement, the SEC withdrew its request to remove Musk from the company's leadership.
Many investors said the penalty would be catastrophic.
"I think this is the best possible outcome for everyone involved," said Tigress Financial Partners' Ivan Feinseth, who gave Tesla a "neutral" rating and called the SEC's punishment a "lenient punishment" for Musk.
"It's important for Tesla that he's still the CEO. ”
Neither Musk nor Tesla admitted or denied the SEC's allegations in the settlement agreement and did not immediately respond to requests for comment.
The settlement agreement still needs to be approved by the court.
Beijing Morning News (Reporter Wang Ping) Beijing Morning Post reporter recently learned from Beijing Construction Engineering Group that one of the core buildings of the 2019 Beijing World Horticultural Exhibition Park - - Beijing World Horticultural Exhibition Performing Arts Plaza project will use multi-color ETFE puzzle membrane structure for the first time, 5440 square meters of membrane structure will present dark red, dark green, orange, blue, red, green 6 colors, in the tension of the cable steel strand to present the shape of "butterfly wings".
According to Liu Changbao, the project leader of Beijing Construction Engineering Fifth Construction Group, the construction area of the Performing Arts Plaza project is 4,500 square meters, the total amount of steel installed is 1,182 tons, and the steel structure roof is supported by 26 cantilever steel trusses arranged in the form of umbrellas, showing the shape of "butterfly wings" under the tension of the cable steel strand.
"Looking down at the Performing Arts Plaza from the air, the gorgeous and colorful roofs are like colorful butterflies dancing through flowers, and the bright colors will not fade due to the passage of time, wind, frost, rain and snow."
Previously, the monochrome ETFE membrane structure has been widely used in Bird's Nest, Water Cube and other projects, but the ETFE membrane structure with multi-color puzzles is the first case in China.
The reporter learned that because there are very few suppliers in the world with a variety of color film structure production capacity, every inch of film structure materials are very "precious".
Liu Changbao said that in order to avoid problems such as overlapping and "fighting" at the end of the cable head, the "double-horned" cable head structure will also be innovatively adopted, and the special fixing insert will ensure that the "fighting" cable head is tied in the correct position.
At present, the construction of the 2019 Beijing World Horticultural Expo Park is underway.
Among them, the International Pavilion project has completed the hoisting construction of all "flower umbrellas".
According to the plan, the project will be ready for installation at the end of October.
