Chinanews.com, October 1 According to Japan's Kyodo News Agency, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe has entered the final stage of discussion for the cabinet reshuffle and high-level party personnel adjustment on the 2nd.
Currently, we are coordinating the appointment of former Minister for Economic Revitalization of Abe's close confidant, Toshiaki Gan, as chairman of the Election Policy Committee or chairman of the General Affairs Committee for the four key positions of the party.
