He served as the chief executive of the Abe Election Policy Headquarters in the party presidential election.
Focusing on the party's four key positions, Abe intends to let Secretary General Toshihiro Nikai and Chairman of the Government Research Committee Fumio Kishida continue to serve.
The chairman of the General Affairs Committee, who is responsible for summarizing the internal party discussions related to the constitutional amendment, and directing the election of the chairman of the House of Councillors next year have become the focus of attention.
