According to the plan, the list of cabinet ministers will be announced in the afternoon, and then the certification ceremony will be held at the palace.
SHANGHAI, Sept 30 (Reuters) - The China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) on Sunday officially released a revised Code of Corporate Governance for Listed Companies, which focuses on further strengthening the constraints on controlling shareholders, actual controllers and their affiliates, paying more attention to the protection of small and medium-sized investors, and actively promoting the participation of institutional investors in corporate governance, drawing on international experience.
The CSRC pointed out that the revised standards cover the basic concepts and principles of governance of listed companies, the composition and operation of shareholders' meetings, the board of directors and the board of supervisors, the rights and obligations of directors, supervisors and senior management, the incentive and restraint mechanism of listed companies, and the code of conduct of controlling shareholders and their related parties.
The new standard also includes the participation of institutional investors and related institutions in corporate governance, the basic requirements for listed companies in terms of stakeholders, environmental protection and social responsibility, as well as information disclosure and transparency.
The revised guidelines require listed companies to implement the development concept of innovation, coordination, green, openness and sharing in corporate governance, increase the requirements for party building of listed companies, and strengthen the leading role of listed companies in environmental protection and social responsibility.
Strengthen the role of the audit committee of the board of directors and establish a basic framework for environmental, social responsibility and corporate governance (ESG) information disclosure.
In addition, in response to the concerns of all parties, the new standard also puts forward new requirements for the stability of control over listed companies, the performance of duties by independent directors, the evaluation and incentive and restraint mechanism of directors, supervisors and senior executives of listed companies, and the strengthening of information disclosure.
The China Securities Regulatory Commission also pointed out that in accordance with the new standards, it will study and improve relevant rules and normative documents, guide self-regulatory organizations such as stock exchanges and the China Association of Listed Companies to formulate and revise relevant self-discipline rules, and gradually improve the system of governance rules for listed companies.
At the same time, strengthen the training of listed companies, strengthen the consciousness of listed companies to improve governance and standardize operation, and continuously improve the quality of listed companies.
