Inner Mongolia import and export links 46 kinds of regulatory certificates all to achieve online verification -Chinanews.com
Hohhot, November 5 (Reporter Li Aiping) Hohhot Customs reported on the 5th that from now on, except for special circumstances such as confidentiality needs, all 46 kinds of supervision certificates in the local import and export links will be verified online.
Enterprises in Inner Mongolia can use paperless methods to declare relevant documents to the customs, avoiding problems such as on-site travel, paper applications, and repeated submissions in the past.
It is understood that the document preparation time refers to the preparation time of various documents required for import and export links before the customs declaration, which is a major factor affecting the overall customs clearance time, in order to compress the customs clearance time and reduce the cost of customs clearance, the documents must be reduced.
Previously, there were 86 kinds of regulatory documents that needed to be verified by the customs in the import and export process, involving 19 departments.
It is reported that this time, in accordance with the principle of "canceling what can be canceled, merging what can be merged, and exiting the port inspection that can be withdrawn from the port inspection", relying on the "single window" platform for international trade, the customs and other 16 issuing authorities have system docking and data interconnection, realizing more data and less errands for enterprises.
According to the customs, in the past, enterprises had to go back and forth to the on-site office hall of the relevant departments to submit paper applications, and the process was long and it was impossible to track the audit status in real time.
Business users can now log in directly to the "Single Window" portal and apply online.
After the certification department has passed the review, the electronic data of the certificate will be transmitted to the customs, and the automatic comparison and intelligent verification of the customs declaration data will be realized in the customs clearance link, and the audit results will be fed back to the enterprise through the "single window", so as to realize the whole process of online handling of regulatory certificate declaration, review, customs clearance and feedback.
The export of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China has soared 20 times in 4 years, or it may be related to the increase in empty nest youth-Chinanews.com
Exports of Korean ginseng and chicken soup to China have soared 20 times in 4 years Analysis: It is related to the increase in empty nest youth
Yonhap News Agency reported on the 5th that last year, South Korea's exports of ginseng chicken soup to China exceeded 100,000 US dollars, an increase of about 20 times compared with 2013 four years ago.
According to the analysis, this growth trend is related to the increase in China's empty-nest youth driving the hot sales of convenience foods, as well as the increase in young people's attention to nutritious meals.
The data was released by the Korea Agricultural, Fisheries and Food Distribution Corporation (aT) on the 5th.
Last year, South Korea's ginseng chicken soup exports to China reached US$100,339 and weighed 21,859 kilograms, an increase of 2,094% and 3,668.8% respectively compared with 2013.
According to the analysis, the increase in sales of Korean ginseng chicken soup in China is related to the increase in the number of empty-nest youths driving the hot sales of convenience foods, as well as the increase in young people's attention to nutritious meals.
As of this year, China's one-person households have exceeded the 200 million mark, and it is expected to increase to 30% of the total population by 2020.
In addition, the analysis also said that avian influenza is the biggest factor preventing ginseng chicken soup from taking root in the Chinese mainland market.
According to the aT, the avian flu outbreak in South Korea from November 2016 to April last year caused the relevant authorities to completely ban the export of ginseng chicken soup to China, resulting in a sharp drop in exports.
In 2016, the export value of ginseng chicken soup to China reached 840,000 US dollars, but last year due to bird flu, the export value plummeted to 100,000 US dollars.
