As Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said, in view of the current positive developments in the relations between the DPRK and the ROK and the DPRK and the United States, China believes that it is necessary for the Security Council to consider initiating the reversible clause at an appropriate time to encourage the DPRK and all parties concerned to take greater steps towards denuclearization.
Looking back, every progress in the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and the peace process requires all parties to show sufficient political courage.
