BEIJING, Nov 5 (Reuters) - The Canton Fair showed that China's foreign trade situation remains complex and severe, with 80.6 percent of companies expecting exports for the full year of 2018 to be better or flat than the previous year, the Canton Trade Center said in a press release on Sunday.
However, considering the continuous rise in the cost of domestic raw materials, labor and other comprehensive factors, and the increasing impact of Sino-US trade frictions, exhibitors also believe that next year's export situation is not optimistic.
At the closing press conference of the 124th Canton Fair, Xu Bing, deputy secretary-general and spokesman of the Canton Fair and deputy director of the China Foreign Trade Center, said that the number of overseas buyers and export transactions at the Canton Fair decreased slightly year-on-year.
There were 189,812 buyers from 215 countries and regions, a year-on-year decrease of 1.11%.
Exports amounted to RMB206.494 billion (US$29.86 billion), down 1% year-on-year.
From the perspective of the market, the transactions of Japan, the 10 ASEAN countries, the "BRIC countries" and South Korea increased by 74.4%, 11.4%, 7.2% and 2.5% respectively, and the traditional markets such as the United States, Australia, Canada and the European Union decreased by 30.3%, 8.9%, 7.3% and 0.8% respectively.
From the perspective of industries, transportation vehicles, machinery and equipment, construction and decoration materials, consumer electronics and information products, and sanitary equipment increased by 24.8%, 21.1%, 20.0%, 15.1%, and 7.6% respectively, while textiles and garments, and household appliances decreased by 13.0% and 6.7% respectively.
Xu Bing said that as a barometer and weather vane of China's foreign trade, the situation of buyers participating in the Canton Fair and the export transaction data show that the development of China's foreign trade will still face many uncertain and unstable factors next year.
However, with the deepening of supply-side structural reform, as well as the recent introduction of national and local policies and measures such as "six stability", the new momentum of China's foreign trade development is accumulating at an accelerated pace, and new progress has been made in the diversification of enterprise markets, which are important foundations and strong conditions for the development of foreign trade.
"Considering all factors, it is expected that China's foreign trade import and export will maintain steady growth throughout the year, and the quality and efficiency will be further improved. Xu Bing said.
