Qingdao, October 1 (Chinanews.com) -- Affected by Typhoon "Tanmei", the 2018 International Extreme Sailing Series Qingdao Station "Mazerun Cup", which was originally scheduled to start on September 30, postponed the first competition day to October 1, and held a pre-race meeting at the Qingdao Olympic Sailing Center before the race, and the captains of 12 hydrofoil catamaran teams from 6 countries and regions all appeared.
Affected by Typhoon "Tanmei", strong winds continued in the harbor, with a maximum wind speed of up to 24 knots, and the departure signal was postponed for nearly 90 minutes from 1 pm on the 30th, and the wind speed still did not decrease, and the chief referee of the event Anne Mundrant announced the cancellation of the first day of the game and postponed the game to the afternoon of October 1.
"The strong winds blowing from the shore continued, and the sea conditions were really violent. ”
Mundrant explains: "In such a situation, no one knows when and with what kind of gusts of wind will blow towards the boat.
With the proximity to the city's venues, canceling the race is the wisest option given the current wind conditions. ”
The crew who were all ready to go was still a little disappointed.
"The boat is ready to stop and we are in good shape. ”
Qingdao helmsman Max Richardson admitted: "But I know it was the right thing to do, and hopefully the wind will be a little less here today and we can show what we can do." ”
Omica Wilkinson, who has been hailed as the "hopeful" of the New Zealand team at Tokyo 2020, said: "Losing a day makes the game even more interesting.
Because the weight of today's game will increase, and there are only two days left.
Everyone will definitely work hard. ”
Despite the strong winds, Pierre Eavis Durand, the helmsman of the French ABM team, appealed at the pre-race meeting about his warm past with Qingdao, where the race was held: he was injured in an accident in the International Extreme Sailing Series five years ago, and his muscles were broken, thanks to the treatment of the local event medical team, he can still stand on the competition venue five years later.
It is reported that the International Extreme Sailing Series was founded in 2007 and is a World Sailing League event with Volvo, America's Cup, World Sailing Confrontation Tour and other events.
The Qingdao race will use the "Flying Ghost" hydrofoil catamaran (FlyingPhantom).
2018 is the 8th year that the event has landed in Qingdao, the "capital of sailing", and Qingdao is also the final battle of the series.
Despite the ongoing volatility in global financial markets, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Monday that the Exchange Fund's investment income in the third quarter of this year fell by 97% year-on-year, but it was better than the previous quarter, as overseas stocks rose amid the trade war between China and the United States, and foreign exchange losses narrowed significantly.
According to the latest data from the HKMA, the Exchange Fund recorded investment income of HK$1.6 billion in July-September 2018, significantly lower than the HK$61.8 billion recorded in the same period last year, but better than the revised HK$100 million in the second quarter of this year.
Mr Norman Chan, Chief Executive of the HKMA, said in the Legislative Council that at the beginning of the US-China trade war, Hong Kong and emerging market equity indices diverged from US stock indices, and it was not until late September and early October that market sentiment began to reverse after US stock market indices peaked one after another, as investors gradually realized that the trade war was also negative for the US itself.
"It's good that there is a change in market sentiment, and if the trade war only has a one-sided effect, it will not help to solve the problem. ”
But he also pointed out that "if the US-China trade war is not resolved, financial market volatility will continue to rise." ”
In the third quarter of this year, the Exchange Fund's loss on equity investments in Hong Kong narrowed by 8% from the previous quarter to HK$4.7 billion, while gains on overseas equities surged by 172% to HK$12.8 billion, while foreign exchange losses of HK$16.2 billion and bond gains of HK$9.7 billion decreased by 24% and 31% respectively quarter-on-quarter, mainly reflecting the general increase in the US dollar against major currencies during the quarter and the rise in US yields above the 3% level in mid-September.
The Exchange Fund is primarily used to support the Hong Kong dollar.
Since 1983, Hong Kong has implemented a linked exchange rate system pegged to the US dollar between the Hong Kong dollar and the US dollar.
Regarding the current financial situation in Hong Kong, Norman Chan said that the uncertainty of the economy and asset markets has increased, and the downside risks have increased, but Hong Kong's financial system is stable, and it is also well defensive, and has sufficient earthquake resistance.
"Hong Kong has a strong international investment position, with a net external value of US$1.4 trillion equivalent to four times GDP, higher than Singapore's 2.5 times and Japan's 0.6 times, and is more than adequate to cope with an economic downturn or reversal. ”
Norman Chan pointed out that the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate rose by more than 400 basis points on September 21, and the market generally believes that it is mainly related to the rise in the Hong Kong dollar interbank rate, and then the Hong Kong dollar hovered around 7.80-7.84 against the US dollar.
However, he believes that with the start of the interest rate hike cycle of Hong Kong banks and the normalization of Hong Kong dollar interest rates, the situation that Hong Kong dollar interest rates are lower than US dollar interest rates will change in the future.
"As Hong Kong dollar interest rates and US dollar interest rates move more in tandem, we must be more careful in managing risks and being prepared for market volatility. ”
The three-month interbank rate fell 0.9% to 2.08179% on Monday, widening its spread with the US dollar from 46 basis points to 51 basis points, while the one-month interbank rate hit a five-month low and widened from 120 basis points to 127 basis points with the US dollar.
From May to mid-September, the spot exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was close to 7.85 per US dollar for most of the time.
During the period, due to factors such as carry activities and the outflow of part of the proceeds from the IPO after the completion of the large-scale IPO activities, the weak-side CU was triggered several times in May and August, following the first triggering in April.
The HKMA buys Hong Kong dollars and sells US dollars at the level of 7.85 under the Linked Exchange Rate System to maintain the stability of the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate.
In May and August, the HKMA bought about HK$52.1 billion under the weak-side Convertibility Undertaking Regime.
Are there any preferential treatments for foreigners under the new IIT Law?
The relevant responsible persons of the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation said in response to reporters' questions on the 30th that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for foreigners, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, when implementing the new individual income tax law.
A reporter asked, the newly revised individual income tax law will adjust the criteria for determining individual income tax resident taxpayers in China from one year to 183 days.
In the next step, when the law is implemented, will there be any preferential arrangements for foreigners, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan?
The person in charge responded that the current regulations for the implementation of the individual income tax law have special preferential provisions on the tax payment of foreigners, and individuals who have no domicile in China but have resided for more than one year and less than five years can only pay individual income tax on the income derived from outside China.
The person in charge said that in order to maintain the stability of the policy, the next step will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas persons, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, when implementing the new individual income tax law.
There is no "threshold" for confinement centers: quality certification promotes quality improvement.
With the pull of the "two-child economy" and the prosperity of the maternal and infant market, from Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou to third- and fourth-tier cities, various grades of confinement clubs have emerged in various places.
At present, the very popular confinement club meets the consumption needs of the masses, and the fees range from tens of thousands of yuan to hundreds of thousands of yuan, but at the same time, it is also in an embarrassing situation.
The State Administration for Market Regulation recently launched a series of activities for the 2018 National "Quality Month", and the reporter came to a five-star confinement center in Tianjin to visit the certification experience of maternal and child care services.
The general confinement center provides newborn care, nutritious meals, postpartum repair and shaping services.
In this confinement center, the reporter saw that nurses checked the breastfeeding of newborns every day, and professional nurses provided fine care services such as bathing and touching for newborns.
At the same time, in order to meet the needs of new mothers, from wound care at the beginning of confinement to body care in the middle and late stages of confinement, we provide traditional Chinese medicine treatment and beauty care and other care items to help mothers restore their slender figure.
A new mother who is staying in the house told reporters that she booked this confinement club 8 months in advance.
The service items of the confinement club directly affect the comfort level and physical recovery of the mother during the confinement period, and some small-scale confinement clubs can only provide some simple confinement services, which have hidden dangers such as non-standard disinfection and hygiene, easy cross-infection, and unscientific diet.
The person in charge of this confinement center said that they are the only one among all the five-star confinement centers in Tianjin that has obtained B-level service certification.
"Although some customers do not understand the meaning of B-level certification at first, it is of great significance to the long-term development of enterprises to benefit customers by forcing enterprises to strictly standardize process management through certification. He said.
Pan Lifen, deputy director of the Certification and Supervision Department of the State Administration for Market Regulation, said that service certification is a new type of certification system based on customer perception and attention to the satisfaction of organizational quality management and service characteristics, which is an important part of the national quality infrastructure and has a positive effect on improving the proportion of high-quality service supply and enhancing the international competitiveness of China's services.
Starting in 2004, after more than 10 years of development, the service certification project has experienced a process of gradual development from scratch, and a number of influential service certifications have emerged, such as financial service certification, maternal and child care service certification, commodity after-sales service certification, e-commerce service certification, health care service certification, etc.
According to the statistics of the State Administration for Market Regulation, there are currently more than 130 service certification bodies in China, more than 2,000 service certification personnel, and nearly 8,000 valid certification certificates.
Pan Lifen said that it is necessary to further guide and promote the development of service certification, gradually expand the coverage of service certification in the fields of health, education, sports, finance, and e-commerce, and promote the supply-side reform and quality improvement of the service industry.
HONG KONG, Nov 5 (Reuters) - Hong Kong property prices have fallen for two consecutive months after peaking, and Norman Chan, chief executive of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, said on Monday that it is still necessary to observe whether the property market has entered a downward cycle, and if confirmed, it can consider gradually easing the tightening of countercyclical measures at an appropriate time.
Norman Chan also pointed out that if property prices rebound, the first people who will be affected will be those who buy homes at the peak of the property market, but it is expected that there will be a sharp drop in property prices such as the Asian financial crisis in 1997, and the chances of people slashing prices and selling properties are much lower.
Speaking at a briefing at the Legislative Council, Norman Chan led a number of senior HKMA executives to say that if it is confirmed that the property market has entered a downward cycle, the measures can be relaxed in due course.
"But now we only see a few weeks of data, it is still too early to relax, and we still need more time to see if the property market has entered a downward cycle. ”
Since October 2009, the HKMA has introduced eight rounds of counter-cyclical measures to significantly tighten mortgages for various types of properties, including lowering the loan-to-value ratio (LTV) ratio and requiring mortgage applicants to pass rigorous stress tests, with a view to enhancing banks' risk management and resilience to earthquakes.
As Hong Kong officially entered the interest rate hike cycle, the private residential property price index in Hong Kong peaked and fell for two consecutive months in August-September, and the month-on-month decline in September widened to 1.44%.
However, the cumulative growth rate in the first three quarters of this year still reached 10.2%.
In the second quarter of this year, the ratio of unsecured owner-occupied households in Hong Kong reached 66%, higher than the average of 60% in 2009-11, and the average loan-to-value ratio and loan-to-income ratio of new mortgages were 47% and 34% respectively, a significant improvement from 64% and 41% respectively in 2009-11.
However, Mr Chan said that high earthquake resilience does not mean that people who have already purchased homes will not be harmed by the economic downturn, as property valuations will fall, and those who buy properties during peak periods will bear the brunt.
While the HKMA has tightened bank lending to mortgage lenders, homebuyers can also obtain high-percentage mortgage loans through mortgage insurance or mortgage loans provided by developers.
Mr Chan said that at present, together with the mortgage loans provided to developers, the loan-to-value ratio of borrowers can reach 85-90%, and if the property price falls by 10%, there will be negative equity (i.e. the market value of the property falls below the total outstanding mortgage loan).
However, the Deputy Chief Executive of the HKMA, Mr Victor Yuen, pointed out that the total amount of mortgages estimated by developers to be in high percentage of mortgages accounted for only 2-2.5% of the total number of bank mortgages, which is still low.
At the peak of negative equity in Hong Kong in 2003, the number of negative equity cases exceeded 100,000, accounting for 22% of the total number of property buyers.
As of the third quarter of this year, Hong Kong has recorded zero negative equity for seven consecutive quarters.
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, October 1 (Liu Hongxia, Ma Rui) E-commerce retail export enterprises ushered in another wave of tax burden on October 1, involving value-added tax, consumption tax exemption and other aspects.
The Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the Ministry of Commerce, and the General Administration of Customs recently jointly issued a document clarifying that the VAT and consumption tax exemption policies shall be implemented on a trial basis for the export of goods exported by e-commerce export enterprises in the Cross-border E-commerce Comprehensive Pilot Zone without obtaining valid purchase certificates, and at the same time meet the following conditions.
First, the e-commerce export enterprise shall register in the comprehensive pilot zone, and register the export date, name of the goods, unit of measurement, quantity, unit price and amount on the cross-border e-commerce online comprehensive service platform of the place of registration.
Second, the export goods shall go through the e-commerce export declaration procedures through the customs where the comprehensive test zone is located.
Third, the export goods do not belong to the goods that the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation have expressly cancelled the export tax refund (exemption) in accordance with the decision of the State Council.
The notice clarifies that the General Administration of Customs regularly transmits the electronic information of the e-commerce export commodity declaration list to the State Administration of Taxation.
The tax authorities in the comprehensive pilot zone shall strengthen the tax exemption management of export goods according to the electronic information of the export commodity declaration list cleared by the State Administration of Taxation.
The circular pointed out that the specific tax exemption management measures shall be formulated by the provincial-level taxation departments in consultation with the financial and commercial departments.
The Office of the Leading Group for the Construction of the Comprehensive Pilot Zone and the competent department of commerce shall coordinate and promote the communication and cooperation between departments and the implementation of relevant policies, accelerate the establishment of a statistical monitoring system for e-commerce exports, and promote the healthy and rapid development of cross-border e-commerce.
Ordos, November 5 (Zhang Linhu) Due to disagreements over the distribution of money, a man in Liaoning Province actually killed his lover and threw his body, and then absconded to the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
On the 5th, the reporter learned from the Public Security Bureau of Dongsheng District, Ordos City, Inner Mongolia, that after a joint investigation by the police of the two places, the man was successfully arrested.
On June 26, 2018, a woman disappeared in Anshan City, Liaoning Province, and her family reported it to the local police.
After the police investigation and judgment, this is not a simple case of missing persons, the missing person Bai is very likely to be killed by his lover Wang, and the police immediately set up a special team for further investigation.
On October 30, the task force found that the criminal suspect Wang might be hiding in Dongsheng District, Ordos City, and the Dongsheng police immediately organized capable police forces to fully cooperate with the Liaoning police to solve the case.
After 5 days of investigation, the police finally figured out Wang's whereabouts and sorted out his related persons in detail.
On November 4, the police of the two places worked together to arrest the criminal suspect Wang in an excavator parts store in Dongsheng District.
According to Wang's confession, he and the victim Bai were lovers, and because Bai's sister had a large amount of money temporarily stored in Bai's name, the two decided to take the money for themselves.
On June 22, 2018, Wang and Bai had a disagreement over the use of the funds, and Wang then killed Bai in a rental house, decomposed the body and threw it away.
At present, the criminal suspect Wang has been handed over to the Anshan police in Liaoning.
