Lawyer carrying an ax to court session?
The news is really exciting at first glance, and it has also exploded in legal circles.
Quanzhou City, Fujian Province, then fined the lawyer 500 yuan and recommended in writing that the Quanzhou Lawyers Association investigate and deal with it.
According to the Beijing News, the Quanzhou Lawyers Association recently issued an official notice saying that the actions of the two lawyers did not involve violations of laws and regulations, and they would not be punished in accordance with the law.
Judging from various reports, the Quanzhou Lawyers Association's handling is not to protect shortcomings or engage in confrontation, but has been recognized by the Quanzhou Intermediate People's Court.
An incident that could have caused tension within the legal community was eventually properly resolved.
The reversal of the matter stems from a more complete restoration of the truth: the axe carried by the lawyer involved was of the same style and model as the defendant's murder weapon, but it was not bladed, and it was only used as auxiliary evidence in the presentation and cross-examination of evidence, and there was no intimidation or subjective intent to "endanger the safety of the court".
There are four very important details that need to be paid attention to in judging whether the lawyer's actions are illegal and illegal: first, the local court only showed a photo of the axe in two previous court sessions, and from the perspective of defense, it is necessary to show the original axe; second, the axe was purchased one hour before the trial, not because the lawyer was unwilling to seek the judge's consent, but objectively failed to contact the judge; third, the entire axe was not excessively or improperly used; and fourth, the lawyer involved publicly admitted his mistake and apologized to the court at the first time.
Based on these circumstances, it can be seen that the lawyer involved "appeared in court with an axe" and had nothing to do with evil, but only to defend himself.
After clarifying the entire facts, the Quanzhou Lawyers Association did not push the boat with the flow, but withstood the pressure and made a decision not to punish.
And this decision can also stand the test of facts and law.
As for bringing an axe as a controlled knife to court without the permission of the court, it is indeed easy to cause uneasiness and misunderstanding.
For safety and prudence reasons, the Quanzhou Intermediate People's Court's previous fines and judicial recommendations are understandable.
In order to safeguard the dignity of lawyers and prevent individual courts from making things difficult for lawyers, the Supreme People's Court promulgated the Rules for Security Inspections of the Judicial Police of the People's Courts in 2014, establishing the principle that lawyers do not need to undergo personal safety inspections when they appear in court.
Since the promulgation of the rule, the majority of lawyers have set an example, and there have been few incidents of endangering court security due to security loopholes.
In rare cases like Quanzhou, as long as communication is carried out in a spirit of mutual respect and understanding, misunderstandings can be resolved.
As a self-regulatory organization of the lawyer profession, the lawyers association undertakes the dual mission of punishing lawlessness and ensuring legality.
In the past, individual lawyers' associations have been criticized for their emphasis on punishment and lack of protection.
The decision of the Quanzhou Lawyers Association, both in terms of process and results, is commendable, and has set an example for more lawyers associations to perform their duties correctly.
From October 1st, what tax benefits will affect our money bags?
Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, October 1 (Reporter Sang Tong) The new individual income tax law will come into force on January 1, 2019, in order to allow the masses of people to enjoy the tax reduction dividend as soon as possible, from October 1, the actual wage and salary income of taxpayers will be deducted according to the monthly threshold of 5,000 yuan, and the new tax rate table will be applied.
With the implementation of the new policy, what are the benefits that will affect the people's money bags?
Good 1: The tax reduction of wages and salaries is obvious
Taxpayers who obtain wages and salaries after October 1 can deduct 5,000 yuan/month of basic deduction expenses and apply the new tax rate table, and most taxpayers have different degrees of tax reduction, especially for low- and middle-income people.
According to the tax reduction table of different income groups, after deducting the "three insurances and one housing fund", the monthly income of 8,000 yuan, 10,000 yuan, 20,000 yuan, and 50,000 yuan will be 90 yuan, 290 yuan, 1,590 yuan, and 9,090 yuan respectively, and the corresponding tax reduction ratios will be 73.9%, 61.1%, 49.0%, and 18.8% respectively compared with the monthly threshold of 3,500 yuan.
It is worth noting that due to holidays, the wages that should have been paid in October at the end of September in accordance with the law by various units can be subject to the new basic deduction fee and tax rate table.
To this end, the withholding client software uniformly promoted by the tax department has provided the corresponding tax calculation function, but the corresponding tax still needs to be declared and paid within the statutory declaration period.
Good 2: The distance between the low tax rate bracket has been significantly widened
In addition to raising the threshold, the new tax rate schedule will apply from 1 October.
The seven-level tax rate of wages and salaries is the same as before, and there is no change, but the tax rate range has changed significantly, the range of three lower tax rates of 3%, 10% and 20% has been significantly expanded, the range of 25% tax rate has been reduced, and the range of 30%, 35% and 45% of the three higher tax rates has remained unchanged.
It is worth noting that the tax law has also adjusted the tax rates of production and operation income, of which the lower limit of the highest 35% tax rate has been increased from 100,000 yuan to 500,000 yuan.
This means that sole proprietorships and sole proprietorship partnerships will benefit from the tax reform.
"Judging from the calculation of the personal tax reduction of Shanghai taxpayers in the early stage, the majority of taxpayers will fully feel the dividends of the individual income tax reform, especially the tax reduction for low- and middle-income groups. ”
Lan Min, head of the individual income tax department of the Shanghai Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, said.
Advantage 3: Tax payment services are more convenient and optimized
Since the promulgation of the new individual income tax law, the Shanghai tax authorities have carried out a series of comprehensive and extensive tax publicity actions.
On the one hand, carry out "one-to-one, point-to-point" policy guidance for key tax sources and key enterprises.
The Pudong New Area Taxation Bureau has visited large enterprises such as Apple Trading (Shanghai) Co., Ltd., Alipay (China) Network Technology Co., Ltd., and Red Star Macalline Home Furnishing Group Co., Ltd., which have a large number of employees, a large amount of withholding and payment workload, and a large amount of tax payment. CIIC Shanghai Economic and Technical Cooperation Co., Ltd. collects the concerns of enterprises in a timely manner, responds to their demands, and solves their difficulties.
On the other hand, for the general public and taxpayers, carry out "all-round, multi-dimensional, three-dimensional" tax policy push.
Use the official website of Shanghai Taxation, WeChat official account, Weibo and other channels to push policy hotspots in a timely manner to ensure that policy publicity is in place.
At the same time, from September 28, the Shanghai tax WeChat official account has launched the 12366 intelligent consulting platform to carry out "targeted" intelligent integrated individual income tax reform publicity services through "artificial + intelligent" tax service consultation.
