"Today, Canada, the United States and Mexico agreed on a new trade deal, the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), which will provide our workers, farmers and companies with a high-standard trade deal that will lead to freer markets, fairer trade, and more sustainable economic growth," the statement said. The agreement will strengthen the middle class, create good-paying jobs, and create new opportunities for an estimated 500 million people. ”
