The fifth "Disability Voice Month" is coming, focusing on the issue of sex education for disabled adolescents-Chinanews.com
In recent years, the topic of sex education for adolescents in China has been widely discussed, but the challenges of sex education for adolescents with disabilities are still very daunting.
Recently, a seminar on challenges and practical strategies for comprehensive sexuality education for persons with disabilities was held in Beijing.
How to educate children and young people with disabilities on sexuality became an important topic of the seminar.
According to the Report on the Sexual Knowledge, Attitudes and Behaviours of Children and Youth with Disabilities in China, released at the conference, children with disabilities experience higher rates of sexual harassment and abuse than healthy children.
For children and adolescents with disabilities, more attention is paid to "sexual protection" in society.
The purpose of this symposium is to discuss the promotion of comprehensive sexuality education for children and adolescents with disabilities in China from the three aspects of family support, school education and institutional services, and to provide support for children and adolescents with disabilities from the source, so that they can enjoy the right to love freely like others.
Experts believe that the Chinese public's understanding of the disabled group has always remained at a level that is not deep enough.
Due to traditional attitudes and other factors, comprehensive sexuality education for people with disabilities, especially children and adolescents with disabilities, is not in-depth enough.
However, in recent years, with the support of UNESCO and philanthropists, the practice and realization path of sexual and reproductive health education for the full-cycle and comprehensive development of persons with disabilities in China have made gratifying progress.
According to the report, although children and young people with visual, hearing, intellectual and physical disabilities have more difficulties than the general population in acquiring sexual knowledge and understanding intimate relationships, they have generally developed towards convenience and enrichment.
Organized by the Shanghai Renren Foundation, and co-supported by UNESCO China, Handicap International Alliance (France) Beijing and UNFPA China, the "Seminar on Challenges and Practical Strategies for Comprehensive Sexuality Education for Persons with Disabilities" aims to discuss the practice and realization path of sexual and reproductive health education for the comprehensive development of persons with disabilities in the context of the Healthy China Strategy, and to promote policymakers, educators, researchers, social service organizations, and social service organizations in the field of special education and inclusive education. Parent representatives and other stakeholders learned about the international policy on comprehensive sexuality education and the right to health of children and youth with disabilities, and exchanged views on sexuality education practices, strategies, challenges and resources for children and youth with disabilities in the country, and discussed and developed a blueprint for comprehensive sexuality education for children and youth with disabilities in the future, forming a support network.
BEIJING, Sept 30 (Reuters) - The central bank's short foreign currency positions against local currency forwards and futures contracts were zero for the 12th consecutive month to the end of August, with no long positions in the month, according to data released by the People's Bank of China on Sunday.
According to the central bank's previous data, as of the end of August last year, the central bank held a total of 6.044 billion US dollars of short positions in foreign currency against local currency forward contracts and futures contracts, unchanged for the fourth consecutive month, and the size of short positions denominated in SDR (Special Drawing Rights) was 4.276 billion SDRs.
Since then, the central bank's short position in FX forwards has been zero.
The data was first released by the central bank at the end of March 2016, and the data showed that at the end of February 2016, the central bank had a long position of $2.438 billion and a short position of $28.9 billion against local currency forwards and futures contracts.
The September data released at the end of October of the same year showed a net increase of $16.401 billion to $45.301 billion for the first time.
The central bank has previously stated that the forward and futures short positions of foreign currency against local currency mainly reflect the foreign exchange forward operations carried out by the central bank with commercial banks in order to meet the hedging needs of foreign currency liabilities of enterprises, and will continue to provide forward hedging products according to the principle of actual demand, and the forward operations of the central bank will have little impact on the scale of foreign exchange reserves in the future.
