At 8:05 a.m. yesterday morning, two pickpocketing suspects were caught pickpocketing from Yongdingmen Station to Zhushikou Station of Bus No. 20.
Two pickpocketing men cut the pockets of the passengers' coats and stole 800 yuan in cash, so that the police, who were already squatting nearby, could catch them.
This is the first pickpocketing case cracked by the Beijing police during the National Day holiday.
At about 5 o'clock yesterday morning, the anti-pickpocketing investigators of the Beijing Public Security Mobile Investigation Corps arrived at the predetermined position.
According to past experience, places where the flow of people is concentrated, bus hubs, bus and subway lines, and the crowd watching the flag-raising in Tiananmen Square are the focus of their work.
In the midst of the crowd, plainclothes policemen calmly observed the passing crowd.
At around 7 o'clock in the morning, investigators who were squatting at the bus stop found two suspicious men following a male passenger from Yongdingmen Station to the No. 20 bus.
In the car, two suspicious men, one left and one right, sandwiched the male passenger in the middle, one of whom tried to cover the other.
But they didn't know that their every move had already fallen into the eyes of the plainclothes policemen who were observing from the sidelines.
In the process of waiting for the man to start the theft, the police stared intently at the man who was ready to pickpocket, and was caught by the investigators in one fell swoop after they succeeded in pickpocketing.
A reporter from the Beijing Morning Post saw that the police seized 800 yuan in cash from the theft suspect.
"The money was taken from the pockets of the passengers' clothes. ”
The police pointed to a torn jacket pocket and said: "They cut this place open and pickpocketed 800 yuan from a tourist who came to Beijing, and when we caught them, the money had just been put into their own pocket." ”
The reporter learned that in order to catch these two people, the plainclothes police followed them for an hour, and finally arrested them in one fell swoop when they committed the crime.
The two suspects are currently under police scrutiny.
Plainclothes police told reporters that the question of who was suspicious in the crowd was very simple for the police.
"If you catch more thieves, you will find that their eyes and demeanor are different from ordinary passengers, in addition to staring at people's pockets and backpacks, they also like to drill into the crowd instead of avoiding people. ”
The police also told reporters that suspects often have no purpose in waiting for the train, and like to wander around the station, and will only follow them on the train after finding the object of pickpocketing.
"These are all empirical words, and after a long time of dry clothes, you will naturally know it. ”
In addition, the police also reminded that "it is most convenient to put things in the pocket of the coat, and it is also the easiest to be stolen." ”
Be careful of your belongings during the ride to prevent theft.
