British Prime Minister Theresa May on Sunday called on her party to unite in support of her Brexit plan, calling directly on critics to support it, saying that the free trade deal they want is at the heart of her Brexit plan.
British Prime Minister Theresa May attends a Conservative Party meeting in Birmingham, England, September 30, 2018.
At the start of the Conservative Party's flamboyant annual conference, Theresa May's plans were again slammed by two former cabinet ministers, including former Foreign Secretary Boris Johnson, who called May's plans "out of order".
But she has also garnered strong support from other pro-Brexit ministers, who have "praised Theresa May as one of the most polite people", and International Trade Secretary Fox and Foreign Secretary Hunt have directed their anger at the EU.
Theresa May's already fragile leadership came under further pressure this month after the European Union rejected parts of the so-called "Chequers" plan.
But May viewed the consultations positively, saying she was prepared to take into account the EU's misgivings.
"My message to my party is that let's work together to find the best deal for the UK," May said.
Former British Foreign Secretary Boris Johnson called Theresa May's plans "out of order" and slammed her for not having confidence in Brexit.
He and former Brexit Secretary Davies are pushing for a Canadian-style free trade agreement with the EU.
Theresa May said the proposal would allow Northern Ireland to implement different tariffs, similar to Northern Ireland's separation from the United Kingdom.
After 6 years, Tencent welcomes major organizational structure adjustments and makes it clear that it will not lay off employees-Chinanews.com
On the 30th, Tencent announced the official launch of a new round of overall strategic upgrading, and the organizational structure ushered in a new round of optimization and adjustment after a lapse of six years, reorganizing and integrating the original seven business groups (BG) into six, and said that the adjustment would not involve layoffs.
Tencent's new six business groups.
After a realignment in six years, two new business groups appeared.
It is understood that the new business group not only maintains the advantages and characteristics of deep cultivation in the vertical field, but also retains the original enterprise development business group (CDG), interactive entertainment business group (IEG), technical engineering business group (TEG), and WeChat business group (WXG); It also focused on the convergence effect, and newly established the Cloud and Smart Industry Group (CSIG) and the Platform and Content Group (PCG).
The reporter noticed that Tencent's original mobile Internet business group (MIG) and the original network media business group (OMG) have disappeared, especially OMG, which is very well-known to the outside world.
Tencent said that the newly established Platform & Content Group (PCG) will organically split and reorganize the original Social Network Group (SNG), the former Mobile Internet Group (MIG) and the former Online Media Group (OMG), which are highly related to social platforms, traffic platforms, digital content, core technologies and other sectors with high integration.
The newly established Cloud and Smart Industries Group (CSIG) will integrate industry solutions such as Tencent Cloud, Internet+, smart retail, education, healthcare, security, and LBS to promote the digital upgrade of the industry.
Ma Huateng, Chairman and CEO of Tencent, said that the second half of the Internet belongs to the industrial Internet, and in the first half, Tencent will provide users with high-quality services through connection, and in the second half, we will build on this to help the industry and consumers form a more open new connection ecosystem.
Responding to rumors of "layoffs": Make it clear that there will be no layoffs.
After Tencent released the news of the organizational structure adjustment, it was reported that the adjustment would involve layoffs.
Tencent's relevant parties told a reporter from Chinanews.com, "It is clear that this organizational structure adjustment will not involve layoffs. We will translate each business module as a whole, first combine and then optimize. ”
Macron pushes France to apply for the "baguette" to protect French skills-Chinanews.com
Chinanews.com, October 1 According to Reuters, European countries have successively applied for their own unique food heritage, following Belgian beer and Italian Naples crepes, France recently plans to apply for baguettes, included in the UNESCO intangible cultural heritage list.
It is reported that the plan was promoted by French President Emmanuel Macron, and the French Bakery and Pastry Industry Alliance expressed support.
They point out that many of the baguettes now sold are made from mass-produced frozen dough with ingredients other than flour, water, yeast and salt, and that traditional artisanal bakeries are fading, hoping that their listing will preserve the world-renowned French craftsmanship.
