In recent years, there have been incidents of unqualified plastic runways on campuses in many places.
To this end, the Ministry of Education issued a notice requiring that the synthetic material surface sports venues of primary and secondary schools delivered after November 1 this year must implement the new national standard.
The mandatory national standard "primary and secondary school synthetic material surface sports field" led by the Ministry of Education, 26 scientific research institutes and testing institutions participated in the drafting, after more than two years of revision, during which more than 100 expert meetings have been organized, as well as nationwide field visits, sampling inspections, collected hundreds of enterprises in the market products countless verification experiments.
The reporter found that the new national standard not only changed from "national recommended standard" to "national mandatory standard", but also added a lot of content, including thickness requirements, physical properties, aging resistance, inorganic filler content requirements, anti-slip rubber polymer content requirements, surface layer finished product hazardous substance limit, non-solid and solid raw material hazardous substance limit, etc.
In particular, it is worth mentioning that the new national standard has limited the harmful substances that may be produced in the construction of the campus plastic runway, from the original 7 to 18, and has made provisions on the limit of volatile organic compounds in the runway after completion in accordance with the home improvement standard.
For example, the "Limits and Odor Requirements for Hazardous Substances in Cast-in-Place and Prefabricated Surface Layer Products" clearly stipulates the release of harmful substances, requiring that the total volatile organic compounds shall not be higher than 5 mg/m3, formaldehyde shall not be higher than 0.4 mg/m3, carbon disulfide shall not be higher than 7 mg/m3, benzene shall not be higher than 0.1 mg/m3, and the odor level shall not be higher than Level 3.
The new national standard also makes detailed provisions on the sampling requirements, inspection rules, and judgment rules of plastic runways on primary and secondary school campuses.
In addition, the artificial turf on campus has also been included in the scope of compulsory testing of the national standard for the first time.
In the near future, all localities should carry out special work arrangements for the implementation of the new national standard, and report the implementation of the new national standard to the Department of Physical Education, Health and Art Education of the Ministry of Education within the year.
Chengdu, September 30 (Wang Yu) On the afternoon of the 30th, the 2018 Women's Table Tennis World Cup finals staged the "National Table Tennis Civil War".
In the end, Grand Slam winner Ding Ning defeated her teammate Zhu Yuling who was fighting at home 4:0 and won the Women's Table Tennis World Cup again after four years, which is also the 21st time that Chinese women's table tennis has won the championship of this event.
Ding Ning and Zhu Yuling are teammates and friends, and both sides are quite familiar with each other's skills and tactics.
Whether it's preparing for the game or warming up before the game, both sides are with each other.
Entering the finals, the two coincidentally said that they had completed the task of the competition.
But the contest between Ding Ning and Zhu Yuling in the game can be called a sword and a sword.
In the first game, Ding Ning, who had the advantage of experience in the competition, took a 3:1 lead at the beginning, and then Zhu Yuling chased the score to 3 with the help of Ding Ning's mistake.
Then Zhu Yuling's mistakes in the offense began to increase, and Ding Ning seized the opportunity to score 3 points in a row to lead 9:5, and took the lead in getting the game point 10:6.
Although Zhu Yuling chased 3 points in a row, Ding Ning still used the serve to win the first game 11:9.
In the second game, Zhu Yuling's mistakes were still high, and Ding Ning took a 6:1 lead with the help of his advantage in the stalemate.
When Zhu Yuling fell behind 2:7, she relied on the change of rhythm to score 2 points in a row, and then used the offense to chase the score to 8:9.
At the critical moment, Ding Ning scored 2 points in a row and won another game 11:8.
In the third game, the two started with a tight bite and tied 3:3.
Then Ding Ning made more mistakes in the offense and lost 3 points in a row, but she then used a sharp attack to score 3 points in a row to chase the score to 6 draws.
Zhu Yuling scored 2 points in a row to establish an advantage again, and took the lead in getting the game point at 10:8.
However, Ding Ning's attack was extremely fierce, and after scoring 4 points in a row, he won the third game 12:10.
In the fourth game, Zhu Yuling took a 4:2 lead at the beginning.
But after that, Ding Ning showed a super offensive state, and stopped Zhu Yuling after scoring 4 points in a row.
After returning from the pause, Zhu Yuling found some form and gradually chased the score to an 8:8 draw.
At the critical moment, Ding Ning did not relent, and scored 2 points in a row to get the match point.
As Zhu Yuling returned the ball out of bounds, Ding Ning swept the opponent 4:0 to win the championship.
Ding Ning ended her 14-month title drought by winning the Bulgarian Open last month, and although she said before the tournament that she had no goal for the tournament, Ding Ning said she had done it in the semi-finals in the morning.
In the end, Ding Ning defeated her teammate Zhu Yuling to win her third World Cup title, and she expressed her satisfaction with her performance: "A championship is important for every athlete.
I didn't expect this before the game, I just said that I would fight one game at a time, and I was very satisfied with my performance in the finals. ”
When talking about whether the enthusiastic crowd at home will cause invisible pressure on herself, she said: "I think I handled the pressure of the whole game well, and Ding Ning's performance today was very good, causing me to not find my rhythm. ”
To activate rural consumption, it is necessary to rely on the normalization mechanism to purify the market, guide the demand for healthy consumption, and enhance the sense of gain of farmers' consumption.
In the first half of this year, the retail sales of rural consumer goods increased by 10.5 percent, 1.3 percentage points higher than that of urban areas.
Visited a poor village in a county in the west, there is only one convenience store in the whole village, and when I walked into the store, some of the goods seemed familiar, "Arowana" was marked as "Golden Dragon Oil", "Wangzai" became "Wang Milk", and there were many "cottage" goods.
Over the years, similar phenomena have been frequently exposed, and some fake and inferior goods in rural areas are close to famous brands, with similar names, similar packaging, and fake and real, which is difficult to prevent.
According to a consumer survey report released by a city in the west, the problem of fake goods in rural supermarkets is serious, and 66% of users have bought fake goods in offline supermarkets in towns and villages, of which food accounts for more than half.
The relevant departments rectify the rural market and shout and beat every year, why is the "Li Ghost" still fighting repeatedly?
Unlike urban markets, farmers' awareness of protecting their rights is relatively weak, and many rural areas are located in remote areas and are in blind spots beyond the reach of regulatory forces, so that fake and inferior goods have a breeding ground.
A commodity is in charge of multiple heads, some departments are in charge of prices, some are in charge of production, and some are in charge of the market, with overlapping functions, cracking down on counterfeits every year, and centralizing the management of a gust of wind, fakes have avoided the limelight, and slowly emerge again.
The lack of a long-term regulatory mechanism, the difficulty of purifying the rural market, the low cost of violating the law, and the large benefits, have caused some illegal traders to start the crooked brains of "going to the mountains and going to the countryside", and some rural areas have become "waste markets".
From subsistence and clothing to moderate prosperity, the vast number of peasants are moving towards development-oriented consumption.
A few days ago, the CPC Central Committee and the State Council issued the "Several Opinions on Improving the System and Mechanism for Promoting Consumption and Further Stimulating the Consumption Potential of Residents", which proposed to promote the upgrading of rural residents' consumption ladder, with the aim of allowing the majority of farmers to "be able to consume", "willing to consume" and "dare to consume", so that rural consumption can truly flourish.
On the one hand, it is necessary to deepen reform, eliminate the malpractice of multi-door and multi-headed management of market supervision and administration, adapt measures to local conditions, improve the food safety and product quality supervision network, and constantly reduce the space for making and selling counterfeits in rural areas.
On the other hand, it is necessary to intensify law enforcement, open up the "capillaries" of supervision, and never allow counterfeit and shoddy products to breed and spread in rural areas.
Severe punishment of pit farmers is to protect farmers, no matter how hidden the counterfeiters are, should not become the reason for the breeding of fake and shoddy goods, the relevant departments should clarify their responsibilities, the grassroots supervision force sinks, which link has a problem, it is necessary to investigate the responsibility, so that the counterfeiters, counterfeiters have nowhere to hide.
Strictly control market access, implement strict qualification examination for producers and operators, control the market circulation, let the products come from the right way, go to the road clear, from the source, the root of the way, so that the legal distributors can operate with peace of mind, so that farmers can buy at ease.
To activate rural consumption, it is necessary to guide the demand for healthy consumption.
With the upgrading of consumption, many farmers not only pursue full food and good food, but also pursue high-quality life such as culture and health, and cannot equate the rural market with "low quality" and "cheap".
It is necessary to promote the extension of e-commerce coverage to the vast rural areas, smooth the two-way linkage sales channels between urban and rural areas, promote the combination of offline industrial development platforms and online e-commerce trading platforms, and support the expansion of new forms and models of consumption to the rural market; promote qualified towns and towns to organically combine trade and logistics with leisure agriculture, rural tourism, product processing, etc.; improve the modern rural circulation network system, optimize and integrate the stock of facilities and resources, and effectively reduce the cost of rural circulation.
Create a clear and reassuring market environment for rural areas, so that farmers do not worry about consumption, rural consumption can become more and more prosperous, and only then can farmers' sense of gain and happiness in consumption be enhanced.
From November 1, China will reduce the most-favored-nation tariff rate on some goods, and the overall tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%
According to the decision of the 26th executive meeting of the State Council, the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council issued an announcement on November 30, 2018, reducing the most-favored-nation tariff rate for some commodities from November 1, 2018.
According to the Announcement of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council on Reducing Import Tariffs on Certain Commodities, in order to adapt to industrial upgrading, reduce enterprise costs and meet the needs of the masses for multi-level consumption, the MFN tariff rate for some industrial products and other commodities will be reduced from November 1 this year.
A total of 1,585 tariff items were tariff-reduced goods, accounting for about 19% of the total number of tariff items in China, and the average tax rate was reduced from 10.5% to 7.8%, with an average reduction of 26%.
The tax reduction mainly involves textiles, stone, ceramics and glass products, some steel and base metal products, mechanical and electrical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, construction machinery, power transmission and transformation equipment, electrical equipment, instrumentation, etc., resource commodities and primary processed products, such as non-metallic minerals, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, gems and jade, etc.
At the same time, with the reduction of the overall level of tariffs, especially the import tariffs on pharmaceuticals and consumer goods, the tariffs and tax rates of import taxes on imported goods will be lowered accordingly.
In order to implement the decisions and arrangements of the CPC Central Committee and the State Council, China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs since May 1 this year, reduced import tariffs on automobiles and parts and some daily consumer goods since July 1, and implemented the third step of tariff reduction for products expanded by the information technology agreement.
This reporter learned from the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council that since the beginning of this year, after many successive independent adjustments, China's overall tariff level will drop from 9.8 percent in the previous year to 7.5 percent, with an average reduction of 23 percent.
Appropriately reducing tariffs is conducive to promoting the balanced development of foreign trade, promoting a higher level of opening up, and is also conducive to the overall use of international and domestic resources and promoting domestic supply-side structural reform.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year is the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up, and taking the initiative to reduce the overall level of tariffs is a practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia, and it is also an important measure for China to further expand opening up and actively expand imports according to its own high-quality development needs.
On September 29, the regional public brand conference of "Huanxiang people" agricultural products in Huanxian County, Gansu Province was held in Nankai District, Tianjin.
Red Army millet, black beans, mountain boy pastoral black goat, hardcover tartary buckwheat tea, paper-cut shadow book, handmade slippers ... A piece of beautifully packaged agricultural products were neatly placed on the booth, and they had a common brand name called "Huanxiang People".
"Building the regional brand of 'Huanxiang people' has effectively solved the development bottleneck of 'many and scattered, small and weak' agricultural products in Huanxian County, and has become a powerful carrier for poverty alleviation. On the 29th, the "Huanxiang People" regional public brand conference of agricultural products hosted by Huanxian County, Gansu Province was held in Nankai District, Tianjin.
Huanxian County is located at the junction of Shaanxi, Gansu and Ningbo provinces, as "the national advanced county of grain production", "the hometown of China's small grains" and "the hometown of China's shadow puppetry", with a long history and rich resources.
Local snacks such as lamb, yellow rice wine, buckwheat chopped noodles, and swallow noodles are the flavors that wanderers in other places often think of.
With the continuous improvement of China's urbanization level and the rapid increase of urban population, a large number of young people in rural areas have left their hometowns to start urban life.
Yang Qiaojia, an expert in China's agricultural brand research, said: "Now the city life is fast-paced and stressful, and more and more people are beginning to miss the rural life when they were children, but, "the hometown that can't go back is called the hometown, and the most beautiful memory is the countryside". ”
Huanxian County has special climatic conditions, long sunshine hours, large temperature difference between day and night, and unique planting conditions for characteristic small grains.
It is rich in more than 20 kinds of small grains, and is the hometown of small grains in China, with the output ranking first in Gansu and the quality in the forefront of the country.
Wang Xiaoli is a girl from Huanxian County who went to school in Tianjin, and participated in the promotion meeting as a volunteer, she said: "The people in the hometown are the closest, and the taste of the hometown is the most beautiful. ”
Dr. Tan Bin, a researcher at the Academy of Science of the State Food and Material Reserves Administration, said that through the detection of more than 900 sets of index data, the testing data of buckwheat, tartary buckwheat, black beans and other agricultural products in Huanxian County have outstanding advantages, and the content of many physiologically active substances in miscellaneous grains is higher than the standard data.
Chai Chun, secretary of the Huanxian County Party Committee, said that through the release of the "Huanxiang people" brand, it can further enhance the quality, standardization and large-scale innovation and development level of high-quality agricultural products in Huanxian County, which is conducive to shaping a good overall image of Huanxian agricultural products and rapidly enhancing visibility, competitiveness and added value.
Canada's gross domestic product (GDP) rose more than expected by 0.2% in July from the previous month, raising expectations that the Bank of Canada will raise interest rates next month.
If it does, it will be the fifth time the central bank has raised rates in a little over a year.
Analysts polled by Reuters had expected a 0.1% increase.
Statistics Canada said Friday that 12 out of 20 industries saw growth.
The data is noteworthy because the central bank expected earlier this month that temporary factors could weigh on Q3 GDP data.
Bank of Canada President Poloz promised on Thursday that the central bank will continue to raise interest rates gradually and will keep a close eye on economic data.
The Bank of Canada's next interest rate decision will be on October 24.
With Canada's economy strengthening and unemployment near record lows, the Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017.
Stephen Brown, senior Canadian economist at Capital Economics, said the country's economy is expected to grow at an annualized rate of about 2% in the third quarter.
"This would be higher than the 1.5% expected by the Bank of Canada and would therefore be another reason to expect the Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month," he said in a note.
Overnight index swaps showed that the market's estimate of the probability of the Bank of Canada's interest rate hike in October rose from 76.46% to 78.27%.
For the first time in 65 years, the ROK and the DPRK jointly inspected the estuary of the Han River
The South Korean Ministry of National Defense confirmed on the 5th that South Korea and the DPRK launched a joint inspection of the waters of the Han River and the Imjin River estuary on the same day.
This measure is a preliminary preparation for ensuring the free navigation of civilian vessels on both sides.
According to a briefing provided to the media by the South Korean Ministry of Defense on the same day, this is the first time that the two sides have conducted a joint inspection of the Han River estuary since the signing of the Korean War armistice agreement in 1953.
The ROK and the DPRK signed a military agreement in September this year, agreeing to jointly inspect the estuary of the Han River and other waters from November in order to ensure environmental protection and tourism development in the future.
In October, the two Koreas planned a joint survey of the waters at a general-level meeting.
On November 5, the joint inspection of the waters of the ROK and the DPRK was officially launched.
The joint delegation consisted of 20 people, including the ROK and DPRK military and experts.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, during the inspection, personnel on both sides did not carry weapons, and it was forbidden to use words and deeds that provoked the other side.
"Because there is no military demarcation line near the estuary, this area used to be an area of high risk of accidents, but through joint investigations, it will become a new peaceful area in the future. ”
The total length of the waters for the joint inspection is about 70 kilometers, with a total area of about 280 square kilometers.
According to the ROK Ministry of National Defense, the ROK will send six research vessels to survey the depth of the sea and provide basic information for safe navigation in the waters.
The two Koreas held a summit meeting in Pyongyang in October 2007 and agreed on joint use of the Han and Imjin estuaries to the sea, but subsequent talks were stalled due to tensions on the peninsula.
According to the military agreement signed between the two Koreas in September, ships from both sides will need to inform each other in advance before sailing in common waters in the future.
Chinanews.com, November 5 According to the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia on the 4th, recently, Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost contact during their travel in Mongolia.
It is understood that the two are members of the blue sky rescue team, on October 19, the two contacted relatives and friends in China, saying that they were about to enter the mountains near Kusugul Lake to explore, and shared their location through WeChat, and then lost contact and are suspected to have gone to no man's land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to the protection of the legitimate rights and interests and safety of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, and has attached great importance to consular protection and assistance.
After learning the news of the disappearance of the above two tourists, the embassy immediately activated the emergency plan for consular protection, and strived to seize the golden rescue time and make every effort to carry out the work.
The embassy maintained close communication with the families of the victims, assisted the families in immediately reporting the case to the Mongolian police, and provided the families with a list of interpreters for selection.
The embassy immediately met with the heads of the Ministry of Foreign Relations, the General Police Department and the General Emergency Situation of Mongolia to report on the relevant situation, and asked the Mongolian side to carry out the search and rescue as soon as possible, and maintain close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure that the latest progress is grasped in a timely manner.
At the same time, the embassy assisted the families in issuing missing person notices in Mongolia, and extensively mobilized overseas Chinese and Chinese-funded enterprises in Mongolia to actively participate in the search for the missing persons, provided effective clues, and provided relevant assistance to a number of blue sky rescue team members who went to Mongolia to assist in the rescue.
With the vigorous promotion of the embassy, the Mongolian side immediately dispatched a rescue team and promised to waive the search and rescue fees.
The Mongol Police and the General Directorate of Emergency Situations instructed the Khuvsgul Provincial Police and the Emergency Situations Department to make every effort to search and rescue.
Because Kuvsgul Lake is located in the northern part of Mongolia and the border with Russia, it is remote, sparsely populated, and the transportation and communication are extremely inconvenient, and Mongolia has entered a severe winter, with the temperature as low as minus 20 degrees, the local police and emergency departments have overcome great difficulties, mobilized almost all police forces, and mobilized local herdsmen to carry out a wide range of carpet search and rescue around the missing location of the two people by riding, walking, visiting herdsmen, etc.
At the same time, in view of the special situation in the pastoral area, the Mongolian side has been circulating the search notice through radio for many days.
The relevant staff of the domestic blue sky rescue team have also come to Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue together with the Mongolian side.
The safety of the two missing people has always been close to our hearts.
So far, the two have been missing for more than 10 days, and the embassy has received some clues one after another, but the two have not been found, and the search and rescue operation is still in full swing.
The embassy will always adhere to the principle of "people-oriented", continue to pay attention to this matter, urge the Mongolian side to continue to make all-out search and rescue efforts, and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties concerned.
The embassy appeals to compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia to contact the Chinese embassy in Mongolia as soon as possible if they know relevant clues.
